INSERT INTO `actions` VALUES (1,'Move',2,'[Untrained, Move, AoO]',NULL,'1 MP (x2 for obstructed terrain, x2 for moving defensively - no AoO)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Move 1 sq.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(2,'Crawl',2,'[Untrained, Move, AoO]',NULL,'2 MP (x2 for obstructed terrain)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Crawl 1 sq.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(3,'Walk',2,'[Untrained, Move, AoO]',NULL,'Full round',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'You can walk a number of squares equal to your adjusted speed.\\nObstructed squares count double.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(4,'Jog',2,'[Untrained, Move, AoO]',NULL,'Full round',NULL,'1 SP',NULL,NULL,NULL,'You can jog a number of squares equal to 2 times your adjusted speed.\\nObstructed squares count double.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(5,'Run',2,'[Untrained, Move]',NULL,'Full round','C','2 SP',NULL,NULL,NULL,'You can run a number of squares equal to 3 times your adjusted speed.\\nReduce your normal maneuverability by one step.\\nYou cannot run through obstructed squares, and while running, you can only use passive DeC.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(6,'Sprint',2,'[Untrained, Move]',NULL,'Full round','C','4 SP',NULL,NULL,NULL,'You can sprint a number of squares equal to 4 times your adjusted speed.\\nReduce your normal maneuverability by two steps.\\nYou cannot sprint through obstructed squares, and while sprinting, you can only use passive DeC.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(7,'Stand Up',2,'[Untrained, Move, AoO]',NULL,'4 MP',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'You stand up from prone.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(8,'Drop Prone',2,'[Untrained, Move]',NULL,'1 MP',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'You lie down on the ground.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(9,'Melee Attack',3,'[Untrained]','d20 + Str or Dex mod + size mod + skill mod + PAM + AB + other mods vs. DeC','8 + weapon\'s size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)','C, melee weapon','1 SP','Reach',NULL,'1 target','You make a normal attack with a melee weapon against an opponent within reach.\\nIf the defender has a threatening weapon larger than your weapon, you provoke an attack of opportunity from the defender.','S - You deal normal damage.\\nES - Halve DR against this attack.\\nCS - You deal additional damage according to the weapon\'s critical multiplier.\\nF - You miss.\\nEF - You deal normal damage to your weapon (no effect for natural weapons).\\nCF - The defender can try to deflect your attack back on you or against another target adjacent to you both. The defender can make a free attack as if using your weapon with a -4 penalty.',NULL,NULL,1),(10,'Melee Disarm',3,'[Untrained]','Melee attack roll vs. DeC + target weapon\'s size mod','8 + your weapon\'s size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)','C, melee weapon','1 SP','Reach',NULL,'1 target','You try to knock your opponent\'s weapon, shield, wand, or other exposed item out of his hands.\\nIf the defender has a threatening weapon larger than your weapon, you provoke an attack of opportunity from the defender. If this attack of opportunity causes damage, the disarm automatically fails.','S - You hit the weapon, and the defender has to make a Str or Dex check against (5 + damage). If this check fails, the weapon or item is dropped (for every 5 levels of failure, it lands 1 sq further away). If you are doing the disarm with a hand (or other natural weapon with a grip), you can instead choose to grab the weapon or item for yourself.\\nF - The disarm fails.\\nEF - The defender manages to disarm you instead.',NULL,'Attacking weapon is larger than target item: +4 per size category\\nAttacking weapon is smaller than target item: -4 per size category\\nTarget item is exposed but not a melee weapon: +4\\nTarget item is semi-exposed (e.g. necklace, helmet, weapon in scabbard): -4\\nTarget item is held in locked gauntlet or hard to reach or grab (e.g. ring): -10\\nDefender is pinned by attacker: +4',1),(11,'Melee Sunder',3,'[Untrained]','Melee attack roll vs. DeC + target item\'s size mod','8 + your weapon\'s size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)','C, melee weapon','1 SP','Reach',NULL,'1 target','You try to damage or destroy an opponent\'s weapon, shield, or other object. This action does not work against worn armor.\\nIf the defender has a threatening weapon larger than your weapon, you provoke an attack of opportunity from the defender.\\nAlthough there are usually no special effects caused by striking specific body parts, it is possible to do so with this action.','S - You deal normal damage against the object.\\nES - Halve the item\'s DR against this attack.\\nCS - You deal additional damage to the object according to the weapon\'s critical multiplier. Note, however, that most objects are resistant or immune to critical hits.\\nF - You miss.\\nEF - You deal normal damage to your weapon (no effect for natural weapons).\\nCF - The defender can try to deflect your attack back on you or against another target adjacent to you both. The defender can make a free attack as if using your weapon.',NULL,'Attacking weapon is larger than target item: +4 per size category\\nAttacking weapon is smaller than target item: -4 per size category',1),(12,'Melee Trip',3,'[Untrained]','Melee attack roll vs. DeC\\nThen d20 + Str mod vs. d20 + Str or Dex mod','8 + weapon\'s size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)','C, melee weapon','1 SP','Reach',NULL,'1 target','You can attempt to trip an opponent with a natural weapon or with certain melee weapons.\\nIf the defender has a threatening weapon larger than your weapon, you provoke an attack of opportunity from the defender.\\nIf the attack roll succeeds, you make a Strength check opposed by the target\'s Strength or Dexterity check.\\nTrip will only work against creatures within one size category of the attacker.\\nIf a flying creature is tripped, it starts falling (as if unable to maintain minimum forward speed).\\nTrip can also be used to unhorse a mounted opponent. A Ride check can be made in place of the defender\'s Str/Dex check.','If the weapon attack hits, the secondary attack has the following effects:\\nS - The target is knocked prone. For every 5 levels of success, you can choose to move (or actually throw) the opponent one square away, causing damage as if the opponent had fallen the same distance.\\nF - You fail.\\nEF - The target manages to trip you instead.',NULL,'The following modifiers do not apply to the melee attack but to the Str check:\\nTarget is smaller than you: +4\\nTarget is larger than you: -4\\nTarget has more than two legs: -4\\nTarget has Acrobatics skill: -1 syn per 5 lvls',1),(13,'Ranged Attack',4,'[Untrained]','d20 + Dex mod + size mod + range mod + skill mod + PAM + AB + other mods vs. DeC','8 + weapon\'s size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)','C, ranged weapon','1 SP','As per weapon (LoE)',NULL,'1 target','You make a normal attack with a ranged weapon against an opponent within range.','S - You deal normal damage.\\nES - Halve DR against this attack.\\nCS - You deal additional damage according to the weapon\'s critical multiplier.\\nF - You miss. To find out where the weapon lands, roll 1d8 to determine a direction away from the target square, and determine distance by multiplying the weapon\'s base range by d% percent.\\nEF - You deal normal damage to your weapon.\\nCF - The defender can try to deflect your attack against another target adjacent to himself and within your line of effect. The defender can make a free attack as if using your weapon with a -8 penalty.',NULL,'Target is adjacent to ally: -4',1),(14,'Ranged Disarm',4,'[Untrained]','Ranged attack roll vs. DeC + weapon\'s size mod','8 + weapon\'s size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)','C, ranged weapon','1 SP','As per weapon (LoE)',NULL,'1 target','You try to knock your opponent\'s weapon, shield, wand, or other exposed item out of his hands.','S - You hit the weapon, and the defender has to make a Str or Dex check against (5 + damage). If this check fails, the weapon or item is dropped (for every 5 levels of failure, it lands 1 sq further away).\\nF - You miss.\\nEF - You deal normal damage to your weapon.',NULL,'The following modifiers do not apply to the melee attack but to the defender\'s Str check:\\nTarget item is larger than Medium: +4 per size category\\nTarget item is smaller than Medium: -4 per size category\\nTarget item is exposed but not a melee weapon: -4\\nTarget item is semi-exposed (e.g. necklace, helmet, weapon in scabbard): +4\\nTarget item is held in locked gauntlet or hard to reach or grab (e.g. ring): +10',1),(15,'Ranged Sunder',4,'[Untrained]','Ranged attack roll vs. DeC + item\'s size mod','8 + weapon\'s size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)','C, ranged weapon','1 SP','As per weapon (LoE)',NULL,'1 target','You try to damage or destroy an opponent\'s weapon, shield, or other object. This action does not work against worn armor.','S - You deal normal damage against the object.\\nES - Halve the item\'s DR against this attack.\\nCS - You deal additional damage to the object according to the weapon\'s critical multiplier. Note, however, that most objects are resistant or immune to critical hits.\\nF - You miss.\\nEF - You deal normal damage to your weapon.',NULL,'Target item is larger than Medium: -4 per size category\\nTarget item is smaller than Medium: +4 per size category',1),(16,'Ranged Trip',4,'[Untrained]','Ranged attack roll vs. DeC\\nThen d20 + Str mod vs. d20 + Str or Dex mod','8 + weapon\'s size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)','C, ranged weapon','1 SP','As per weapon (LoE)',NULL,'1 target','You can attempt to trip an opponent with certain ranged weapons, such as bolas and lariats.\\nIf the attack roll succeeds, you make a Strength check opposed by the target\'s Strength or Dexterity check.\\nTrip will only work against creatures within one size category of the attacker.\\nIf a flying creature is tripped, it starts falling (as if unable to maintain minimum forward speed).\\nTrip can also be used to unhorse a mounted opponent. A Ride check can be made in place of the defender\'s Str/Dex check.','If the weapon attack hits, the secondary attack has the following effects:\\nS - The target is knocked prone.\\nF - You fail to trip the opponent.',NULL,'The following modifiers do not apply to the ranged attack but to the Str check:\\nTarget is smaller than you: +4\\nTarget is larger than you: -4\\nTarget has more than two legs: -4\\nTarget has Acrobatics skill: -1 syn per 5 lvls',1),(17,'Splash Attack',4,'[Untrained]','d20 + Dex mod + size mod + range mod + PAM + AB + other mods vs. DeC','8 + weapon\'s size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)','C, ranged splash weapon','1 SP','Per weapon (default 2)',NULL,'Per weapon (default 1 sq radius sphere)','You throw a splash weapon at a creature or a square.','S - You deal normal damage to the target.\\nF - You miss. To find out where the weapon lands, roll 1d8 to determine a direction away from the target square, and determine distance by multiplying the weapon\'s base range by d% percent.\\nRegardless of success, roll separate attack rolls (according to the weapon; default +4) against the Ref of creatures in the splash area.',NULL,'Primary target is adjacent to ally: -4',1),(18,'Spray Attack',4,'[Untrained]','d20 + Dex mod + size mod + PAM + AB + other mods vs. Ref','8 + weapon\'s size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)','C, spray weapon','1 SP','0',NULL,'Per weapon (default 1 sq conical burst)','You use a spray weapon against one or more opponents within range. Even throwing sand or flour can be considered a spray attack.','S - You deal normal damage.\\nF - You typically deal half normal damage (depending on the weapon).\\nCF - You deal normal damage to yourself.',NULL,'Target is adjacent to ally: -4',1),(19,'Bull Rush',5,'[Untrained, AoO]','d20 + Str mod + grapple size mod + (Weapons - Brawling skill mod) + PAM + AB vs. opposed d20 + Str mod + grapple size mod + (Weapons - Brawling skill mod) + PAM + DeB','8 + size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)','C','1 SP','Tch',NULL,'1 target','You first move into your target\'s square (paying MP and provoking attacks of opportunity for the move). You then try to push the target out of the square with an opposed Strength check.\\nYou can only Bull Rush opponents that are within two size categories of yourself.','S - The target is pushed back one square. For every 5 levels of success, you can push back the opponent one more square, but you have to move with him and pay 1 additional AP per square moved. Both you and the target provoke attacks of opportunity for this move.\\nF - You are pushed back into the last square you occupied before the attack.',NULL,'Target has more than two legs: -4\\nBull rush with charge: +2',1),(20,'Crush',5,'[Untrained, AoO]','d20 + Str mod + (Weapons - Brawling skill mod) + PAM + AB vs. Ref','8 + size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)','C','1 SP','Tch',NULL,'Your spacing','You first move or jump into the targeted area (paying MP and provoking attacks of opportunity for the move) and fall prone. By doing this, you try to pin and crush the target(s) under your own body.\\nYou can only Crush opponents that are two or more size categories smaller than yourself, since larger creatures can push you out of their square.','S - You crush the target under your body, causing blunt damage according to your size (Tiny 1d4 B, Small 1d6 B, Medium 1d8 B, Large 2d6 B, Huge 3d6 B, Gargantuan 4d6 B, Colossal 5d6 B; add Str mod to the damage).\\nAffected targets are considered grappled until they escape, you move, or you stand up from prone.\\nF - The target moves out of your way (for free) into any adjacent square.',NULL,'Crush with charge: +2',1),(21,'Overrun',5,'[Untrained, AoO]','d20 + Str mod + grapple size mod + (Weapons - Brawling skill mod) + PAM + AB vs. opposed d20 + Str or Dex mod + grapple size mod + (Weapons - Brawling skill mod) + PAM + DeB','8 + size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)','C','1 SP','Tch',NULL,'1 target','You first move into your target\'s square (paying MP and provoking attacks of opportunity for the move).\\nYour opponent can simply choose to avoid you, and in that case, you continue your move out of the square (and action time is reduced by 4 AP).\\nIf your opponent tries to block, you make the opposed check shown above.','S - The defender is knocked prone, and you can choose to continue your movement.\\nIf the target is smaller than you, you can make a free leg attack against it.\\nF - You are pushed back into the previous square.\\nEF - You are pushed back into the previous square and knocked prone.',NULL,'Target has more than two legs: -4\\nOverrun with charge: +2',1),(22,'Initiate Grapple',5,'[Untrained, AoO]','d20 + Dex mod + size mod + (Weapons - Brawling skill mod) + PAM + AB vs. DeC','8 + size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)','C, primary attack(s)','1 SP','Tch',NULL,'1 target','To start a grapple, first make the indicated action check against your opponent. If the attack of opportunity causes damage, the grapple automatically fails. If the target is already grappling with someone else, this check is automatically successful.\\nIf you successfully initiate a grapple with a target two or more size categories larger than you, you are holding onto the target, but the target is not considered grappled (unless it chooses to be).','S - You are now grabbing (but not grappling) the target. Next, make a free grapple attack (see Grapple Attack action). If this attack succeeds, you deal normal grapple damage to the target, move into the target\'s square, and are now grappling with the target. This move provokes attacks of opportunity from opponents other than the target.\\nAs an alternative to dealing damage, the attacker can choose among the other effects listed under the grapple attack action (except pin).\\nIf the free grapple attack fails, the grapple is not successfully initiated.\\nF - You lose the grab and fail to initiate the grapple.',NULL,'More free primary natural attacks than opponent: +4\\nUsing a single primary attack form: -20 (the attacker is not considered grappled; this also means that the attacker can move normally, carrying along all grapplers)',1),(23,'Grapple Attack',5,'[Untrained]','d20 + Str mod + grapple size mod + (Weapons - Brawling skill mod) + PAM + AB vs. opposed grapple attack check','6 + size mod AP (minimum 5 AP)','C','1 SP','Tch',NULL,'1 grappling target','Grapple attacks can only be made after a grapple has been initiated, but they can be made by anyone involved in the grappling.','S - The grapple attack inflicts the same damage as an unarmed attack made by the attacker. To be more specific, this attack can involve an elbow to the face, a claw attack, bending the opponent\'s joints, crushing him with a bear hug, etc. Use the damage modifier either from Weapons - Generic, Weapons - Brawling, or Weapons - Natural, whichever is higher.\\nAlternatively, a successful check can be used to achieve one of the following results:\\n- Draw a light weapon, material component, or other accessible item.\\n- Use a light weapon (already drawn) to deal damage to another grappler as if using a melee attack.\\n- Escape from the grapple and move into an adjacent space. Your check has to beat all opposing grapplers for it to be successful.\\n- Move all grapplers (including yourself) one or two squares. Your check has to beat all opposing grapplers for it to be successful.\\n- Pin another grappler for 1 round. You can only pin one opponent at a time.\\n- Break another grappler\'s pin.\\n- Knock another grappler prone.\\n- Use a light weapon held by another grappler to attack him or another grappler. This first requires a successful grapple check and then a melee attack roll with a -4 attack penalty.\\n\\nOnce you have an opponent pinned, further successful checks can also be used to achieve these results:\\n- Throw the pinned opponent into an adjacent square (if no other grappler is also grappling the same opponent). For every 5 levels of success, you can throw the opponent one square further away, causing damage as if the opponent had fallen the same distance. The thrown opponent is no longer pinned or grappled.\\n- Try to incapacitate the pinned opponent, causing twice the normal grappling damage in SP.\\n- Prevent the pinned opponent from speaking (and using verbal components) until the pin ends.\\n- The pinned opponent can be used as an improvised weapon or shield against non-grappling opponents until the pin ends.\\n- If you have a mouth and are four or more size categories larger than the pinned opponent (or have an improved swallow ability), you can swallow the opponent. This automatically causes bite damage. The opponent is considered grappled even after being swallowed, but the swallower is no longer grappled.\\n\\nF - You inflict no damage.',NULL,'More free primary natural attacks than opponent: +4\\nUsing a single primary attack form: -20 (the attacker is not considered grappled)',1),(24,'Charge Attack',6,'[Untrained, AoO]','As per attack','As per attack + 1 MP per sq moved','C, as per attack','2 SP','As per attack',NULL,'1 target','You move two or more squares directly towards an opponent in line of sight and then make a melee attack with a +2 damage bonus or a brawling attack with a +2 attack bonus. A charge with a melee attack can also be a melee disarm, melee sunder, melee trip, or even a multi-attack.\\nThe movement provokes attacks of opportunity normally, but the attack itself does not.\\nYou must have a clear path across easy terrain for your movement, but please note that Maintain Balance and Jumping actions can be used to allow charging over some types of difficult terrain. The attack must be aimed in the same direction as the move (+/-45 degrees).\\nThe attack must be made with primary attack forms (or with weapons held in primary attack forms).\\nDuring and after a charge, you suffer a -2 DeC penalty (per charge, if multiple charge attacks are made in the same round) until the start of your next turn.\\nSome weapons deal double damage when used in a charge attack and your adjusted speed is 10 or better.\\nSome weapons deal double damage when readied against a charge.\\nCharging can be done with any mode of movement that allows running or sprinting. A flying charge is usually performed as a dive.\\nThe Jump and Dodging actions can also be used as part of a charge attack.','As per attack.',NULL,NULL,1),(25,'Multi-Attack',6,'[Untrained]','Two or more separate weapon attack checks','Var','C, as per attacks','1 SP','As per attacks',NULL,'1 or more targets','You make two or more attacks simultaneously. The maximum number of simultaneous attacks is equal to the number of attack forms or weapons you have. The maximum number of attacks is also limited by your skill levels in the appropriate Weapons skill(s). Each attack carries an attack penalty, but this penalty can be reduced with skill levels in Fighting Style - Multi-Attack.\\nThe total AP cost is the sum of the AP cost of each attack, but with a reduction based on the number of attacks.\\nThe AP reduction and base modifier is...\\nDouble attack: -2 / -6\\nTriple attack: -4 / -8\\nQuadruple attack: -6 / -10\\nQuintuple attack: -9 / -12\\nSextuple attack: -12 / -14\\nSeptuple attack: -16 / -16','As per attacks.',NULL,'Attack with natural weapon: Penalty for that attack reduced by 4\\nAttack with light weapon: Penalty reduced by 2\\nAttack with two-handed weapon: Penalty increased by 4\\nAll attacks against the same opponent: Penalty for all attacks reduced by 2\\nNote that the reduced penalties can never turn the penalty into a bonus.',1),(26,'Melee Coup de Grace',3,'[Untrained, AoO]','Melee attack roll + 20 vs. DeC','12 + weapon\'s size mod AP (minimum 9 AP)','C, weapon','1 SP','1 sq',NULL,'1 helpless target','You use a melee weapon to deliver a coup de grace against a helpless defender.','As per attack. If the attack results in a critical hit, the attacker can make a secondary attack of (d20 + damage dealt) vs. Fort defense (S - defender takes an additional 100 HP of damage).',NULL,NULL,1),(27,'Ranged Coup de Grace',4,'[Untrained, AoO]','Ranged attack roll + 20 vs. DeC','12 + weapon\'s size mod AP (minimum 9 AP)','C, weapon','1 SP','1 sq',NULL,'1 helpless target','You use a projectile weapon to deliver a coup de grace against a helpless defender.','As per attack. If the attack results in a critical hit, the attacker can make a secondary attack of (d20 + damage dealt) vs. Fort defense (S - defender takes an additional 100 HP of damage).',NULL,NULL,1),(28,'Cast Spell',7,'[Su, AoO, Boost, T10]','(d20 + Arcane/Divine/Psi skill + ability mod - total PP cost + PP boost + MAM)','Var','C + var','Var','Var','Var','Var','Var','Var','Var','Var',1),(29,'Counterspell',7,'[Su, AoO, T10]','d20 + Arcane/Divine/Psi skill + ability mod + MAM + PP spent vs. spellcasting check','Reaction or 6 AP','C, V, S','0+ PP','See below','Instantaneous','1 spellcasting target','You try to interrupt the target\'s spellcasting by using the same skill.\\nYou use this action by first readying a Spellcraft action to identify the spell being cast. If you successfully identify the spell, and you know the same spell or are trained in the same skill that the caster is using to cast the spell, you can make a simple opposed skill check against the caster spellcasting check. You may spend any amount of PP (up to your skill level) and add them to your check.\\nA different kind of counterspelling can be used to co-opt an existing spell that someone else is maintaining through concentration. Note that this is an active action and not a ready action. First, you perform an active Spellcraft (Identify Supernatural Effect) action, with a concentrating spellcaster as the target. If you successfully identify the spell, and you know the same spell or are trained in the same skill that the caster used to cast the spell, you can make a simple opposed skill check against the caster\'s spellcasting check. You may spend any amount of PP (up to your skill level) and add them to your check. If you win the opposed check, you co-opt the spell and can control it for as long as you maintain concentration.','S - You interrupt the target\'s spellcasting.\\nCS - You can redirect the spell against a new target (including the caster).\\nF - Your counterspelling fails.',NULL,'Short range: +0\\nMedium range: -4\\nLong range: -8\\nCounterspelling with the right skill but without knowing the spell: -2\\nSpellcraft synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls',1),(30,'Draw Weapon',8,'[Untrained]',NULL,'2 AP','Hand(s)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'You can draw a maximum of one weapon per available hand. The same action is used to draw other items that are kept easily accessible, such as wands, potions, etc.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(31,'Sheathe Weapon',8,'[Untrained]',NULL,'2 AP','Hand(s)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'You can sheathe a maximum of one weapon per available hand. The same action can be used to sheathe other items, such as wands, potions, etc.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(32,'Ready Shield',8,'[Untrained]',NULL,'4 AP','Hand(s)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'You either grasp and ready a shield or loosen and stow it.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(33,'Stow Equipment',8,'[Untrained, AoO]',NULL,'Half round','Hand(s)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'You either retrieve an item from a backpack or other worn container or store an item in such a container.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(34,'Pick up Item',8,'[Untrained, AoO]',NULL,'4 AP','Hand(s)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'You pick up an item from the ground.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(35,'Drop Item',8,'[Untrained]',NULL,'0 AP',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'You drop an item.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(36,'Learn Spell',7,NULL,'d20 + Arcane/Divine/Psi skill + ability mod vs. 20 + (spell\'s or option\'s minimum PP cost)','1 day (50% time)','C',NULL,'Personal',NULL,'One spell/power/option','You try to learn a new spell, power, or spell/power option.\\nYour skill level in all the mandatory skills must be at least equal to the spell\'s or option\'s minimum PP cost. You use your highest mandatory skill level as a bonus on the learning check.','S - You learn the spell (without options) or a new spell option and can start using it.\\nF - You fail to learn the spell or option but can try again the next day.',NULL,'Taught by teacher with appropriate skill and spell knowledge: +4\\nTaught by teacher with appropriate spell knowledge but \"wrong\" skill: +0\\nTaught by writing: +0\\nTaught by self: -4\\nSpellcraft synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls',1),(37,'Defensive Roll',9,NULL,'d20 + Acrobatics skill + Dex mod + PAM + EP vs. 10 + damage dealt','Reaction','C','2 SP','Personal','Instantaneous','You','When you are struck by a weapon attack that would reduce you to 0 HP or less, you can attempt to reduce the damage by rolling with the blow.','S - Halve the damage you would otherwise have taken from the attack.\\nCS - You avoid the attack completely.\\nF - You take normal damage from the attack.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(38,'Dodging',9,'[Untrained, Move]','d20 + Fighting Style - Mobility skill + Dex mod + PAM + 2 x EP vs. DC','2 MP','C','1 SP','Personal','Move one square','You','You weave and dodge in order to confuse opponents and avoid attacks of opportunity.','S - Your movement does not provoke attacks of opportunity.\\nF - You provoke attacks of opportunity normally.\\nNote that you can succeed against some enemies while failing against others.','Dodge through threatened squares: 5 + enemy TL (one check against all enemies)\\nDodge through squares with enemies: 15 + enemy TL (one check against all enemies)\\nMultiple threatening enemies: +2 per enemy beyond the first\\nSloped or angled surface: +2','Fast dodge (1 MP instead of 2 MP): -10\\nAcrobatics synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls\\nAthletics synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls',1),(39,'Escape Hold',9,'[Untrained]','d20 + Acrobatics skill + Dex mod + PAM + EP vs. DC or grapple check','See below','C',NULL,'Personal',NULL,'You','You attempt to escape from some sort of hold or entanglement. This action can also be used to pass through a tight space (wider than your head but narrower than your shoulders).','S - You escape the hold or entanglement (or can at least move up to 2 squares).\\nF - You are still held or entangled. You can try again, however.','Grappler: Grapple check (5 + size mod AP)\\nNet: 20 (10 AP)\\nEntangling magic: 20 (10 AP)\\nTight space: 30 (one check and 1 minute per 2 squares)',NULL,1),(40,'Instant Stand',2,'[Untrained, Move]','d20 + Acrobatics skill + Dex mod + PAM + EP vs. DC','2 MP','C',NULL,'Personal',NULL,'You','You try to stand up from prone much faster than normal.','S - You stand up from prone and do not trigger any attack of opportunity.\\nF - You are still prone and also trigger attacks of opportunity.','Instant stand: 15','Athletics synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls',1),(41,'Land Softly',9,'[Untrained]','d20 + Acrobatics skill + Dex mod + PAM + EP vs. DC','Reaction','C',NULL,'Personal',NULL,'You','When falling or jumping from a height, you try to make a soft landing.','S - One d6 of blunt damage changes from HP to SP. You can choose to land on your feet, or land prone and change one additional d6 from HP to SP.\\nOS - Calculate falling damage as if the height was 2 squares less. You can choose to land on your feet, or land prone and reduce effective height by 4 squares instead of 2.\\nF - Use full height when calculating falling damage. You land prone.','Land softly: 15','Deliberate jump: +5\\nAthletics synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls',1),(42,'Maintain Balance',2,'[Untrained, Move]','d20 + Acrobatics skill + Dex mod + PAM + EP vs. DC','Reaction (part of move)',NULL,NULL,'Personal','1 r','You','Use this action to stay on your feet when standing or moving on slippery or unstable ground.\\nWhile balancing, you are considered flat-footed, unless your skill level is 2+.','S - You remain on your feet and can move normally for one round.\\nF - You fall prone in your current square. You can spend AP to stand up and then try again.','Run/charge on uneven ground or slope: 10',NULL,1),(43,'Perform',10,'[Untrained, T10]','d20 + Acrobatics skill + Dex mod + PAM + EP vs. DC','1 day (50% time)','C',NULL,'LoS',NULL,'Audience','You use your skill in acrobatics to entertain an audience.','S - You impress the audience enough to make money.\\nF - You do not impress the audience and make no money.','Routine performance: 10 (earns 1d6 cp/day)\\nEnjoyable performance: 15 (earns 1d6 sp/day)\\nGreat performance: 20 (earns 3d6 sp/day)\\nMemorable performance: 25 (earns 1d6 gp/day)\\nExtraordinary performance: 30 (earns 3d6 gp/day)\\nUnimpressed audience: +2 per previous failure','Perform synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls',NULL),(44,'Tightrope Walking',2,'[Untrained, Move]','d20 + Acrobatics skill + Dex mod + PAM + EP vs. DC','Part of move',NULL,NULL,'Personal','1 r','You','You move at half speed (2 MP per square) along a rope, ledge, or similar narrow surface.','S - You can move along the surface without falling.\\nF - You fail to make progress along the surface but do not fall down. You can try again next round.\\nCF - You do not make any progress and fall prone (or fall down).','Less than 5 cm wide: 20\\n5-15 cm wide: 15\\n16-30 cm wide: 10\\nAngled: +2','Move at full speed: -5 (1 MP per sq)\\nRun: -20',NULL),(45,'Handle Animal',1,'[Untrained, T10]','d20 + Animal Empathy skill + Cha mod + MAM vs. DC','4 AP','C, V, S',NULL,'Close (LoS)','Var','One trained animal','You try to make a domesticated animal do more or less what it has been trained to do.','S - The animal does what you want.\\nF - The animal hesitates or disobeys. You can try again next round.','Perform a known trick: 10\\nPerform an unknown trick: 25\\nForce the animal to hustle: 25\\nThe animal is wounded, tired, irritated: +2 to +4\\nMonster of animal intelligence: +5','Animal companion: +4 circ',NULL),(46,'Influence Animal',1,'[Mind]','d20 + Animal Empathy skill + Cha mod + MAM vs. DC','1 min','C, V, S',NULL,'Close (LoS)','Instantaneous','One animal','You use body language, demeanor, and vocalization to improve the target\'s attitude towards you.\\nSkill level 5: You can improve the attitude of a monstrous animal.','S - The attitude can be shifted one step (plus one per 5 levels of success).\\nF - The target\'s attitude is unchanged, and it acts accordingly. You can try again, if the situation permits.\\nCF - The target\'s attitude shifts in the opposite direction.','Initially hostile target: 20\\nUnfriendly or indifferent target: 15\\nFriendly target: 20','Target is a monstrous animal: -4\\nRushed attempt (full-round action): -10',NULL),(47,'Domesticate Animal',1,NULL,'d20 + Animal Empathy skill + Cha mod vs. DC','Var (25% time)','C, V, S','Var (feed)','Close (LoS)','Instantaneous','1 to 3 infant animals','You try to domesticate one or more wild animals. Once domesticated, you can train it to perform tricks.','S - The animal(s) become domesticated. Train and Handle Animal can now be used.\\nF - You fail to domesticate the animal. Retrying is not allowed.','Rear wild animal: 15 + TL\\nMonster of animal intelligence: +5\\nAnimal is wounded, tired, irritated: +2 to +4',NULL,NULL),(48,'Train Animal',1,NULL,'d20 + Animal Empathy skill + Cha mod vs. DC','Var (25% time)','C, V, S','Var (feed)','Close (LoS)','Instantaneous','One trainable animal','You train an animal for a specific purpose or teach it a new trick.','S - The training succeeds. You can now use Handle Animal to get the animal to perform accordingly.\\nF - The training fails, but you may try again.','Train for combat riding (6 w): 20 (attack, come, defend, down, guard, heel)\\nTrain for fighting (3 w): 20 (attack, down, stay)\\nTrain for guarding (4 w): 20 (attack, defend, down, guard)\\nTrain for heavy labor (2 w): 15 (come, work)\\nTrain for homing (5 w): 20 (come, fetch, heel, return home)\\nTrain for hunting (6 w): 20 (attack, down, fetch, heel, seek, track)\\nTrain for performance (5 w): 15 (come, fetch, heel, perform, stay)\\nTrain for riding (3 w): 15 (come, heel, stay)\\nTeach a simple trick (1 w): 15 (come, down, fetch, heel, perform, seek, stay, or work)\\nTeach an advanced trick (1 w): 20 (attack, defend, guard, track, return home)\\nTeach unusual movement (1 w): 25 (aerial or aquatic movement through magic)\\nMonster of animal intelligence: +5\\nAnimal is wounded, tired, irritated: +2 to +4','Animal companion: +4 circ',NULL),(49,'Jump',2,'[Untrained, Move, T10]','d20 + Athletics skill + Str mod + PAM + EP','1 MP per sq',NULL,'1 SP','Personal',NULL,'You','You attempt to jump a certain vertical or horizontal distance. Unless you want to land prone, you have to accept a penalty (see below).\\nA running jump requires moving at least 4 sq in a straight line.\\nIf you have a suitable pole (note that a quarterstaff or spear qualifies) and a place to plant it, you can turn a running jump into a pole vaulting jump. Pole vaulting is more difficult, but it lets you add the pole\'s length to either the vertical or horizontal distance cleared.\\nCreatures with natural swim speeds can use the Jump action to jump above the surface, but they take a -10 penalty on the Jump check.','With a standing long jump, you can cover a horizontal distance of check x 0.15 m. You clear a vertical height 1/4 of the horizontal distance.\\nWith a standing high jump, you can clear a vertical height of check x 0.05 m.\\nWith a running long jump, you can cover a horizontal distance of check x 0.3 m. You clear a vertical height 1/4 of the horizontal distance.\\nWith a running high jump, you can clear a vertical height of check x 0.1 m.\\nIf your check is 0 or less, you stumble and fall prone at the start of the jump.\\nIf you are trying to grab rather than clear something (such as a ledge or hanging rope), add your height (based on size and body type) to the vertical result. After grabbing such a target, a DC 15 climb check is required to pull oneself up.',NULL,'Speed modifier: -12 + 2 x (base speed in squares)\\nLand on feet: -5\\nPole vaulting: -5\\nAcrobatics synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls',1),(50,'Climb',2,'[Untrained, Move, AoO]','d20 + Athletics skill + Str mod + PAM + EP vs. DC','Depends on race','Hands and feet','1 SP per r','Personal','1 r','You','If your race has the climbing trait, this action can be used to scale a cliff, a wall, or a steep slope.\\nYou need both hands and feet to climb, but you can cling to a wall with one hand and use the other to make attacks or cast somatic spells.\\nWhile climbing, you can only use passive DeC (unless your race has a climb speed).','S - You can use your MP to climb up, down, or across.\\nF - No climbing progress. You can try again next round.\\nOF - You fall.','Less than 60 degree incline, or knotted rope and wall: 0\\nRope and wall, or knotted rope: 5\\nRigging, or surface with edges: 10\\nSurface with handholds, unknotted rope, or pulling oneself up on a ledge: 15\\nUneven surface, typical dungeon wall: 20\\nNatural cliff, or brick wall: 25\\nOverhang, or ceiling with handholds: 25\\nSmooth, flat, vertical surface: 40\\nIf you can create your own handholds (with pitons or an axe), the DC becomes 15, but this takes 1 min per handhold.\\nRappel down with rope and climber\'s kit: 10 for 1 MP per sq, 20 for 1/2 MP per sq\\nBracing against opposite wall: -10\\nBracing against corner wall: -5\\nSlippery: +5\\nCatch yourself when falling: +15\\nCatch someone else falling: +10','Fast climb (halve MP per sq): -5\\nVery fast climb (1 MP per sq): -20\\nRetain active DeC while climbing: -20\\nRacial climb speed: +8 racial\\nClimber\'s kit: +2 circ\\nAcrobatics synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls\\nSurvival synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls',1),(51,'Swim or Dive',2,'[Untrained, Move, T10]','d20 + Athletics skill + Str mod + PAM + 2 x EP vs. DC','4 MP per sq','Arms and legs','1 SP per min','Personal','1 r','You','Even without a racial swim speed, you can swim through water (on the surface or under it) by spending 4 MP per sq. You can swim twice as fast as normal, but this increases the cost to 1 SP per round.\\nUnless you can breathe water, you have to hold your breath whenever you are under the surface (intentionally or unintentionally). See the rules for holding breath and suffocation.','S - You can use your MP to move through the water.\\nF - You fail to make any progress and take 1d3 SP. You can try again next round.\\nEF - You are unable to remain afloat and start to sink.','Calm water: 10\\nRough water: 15\\nStormy water: 20 (taking 10 is not possible)\\nFast-moving water: 15 (rocks and cascades can deal physical damage)','Racial swim speed: +8 racial\\nSurvival synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls',1),(52,'Appraise',1,'[Untrained, Secret]','d20 + Crafting skill + Int mod vs. DC','1 min','Vision',NULL,'Tch',NULL,'1 object, performance, or creature','You try to estimate the monetary value (and authenticity) of an object, a performance, or a creature.\\nAlternatively, you can use this action to determine which race made the object.','S - You estimate the value within +/-10%.\\nF - You fail to estimate the value. If you have training in the skill and are appraising a common object, you can still make an estimate within 50% to 150% (2d6+3 x 10%) of the true value. Retrying is not possible until your skill improves.','Basic trade good: 5\\nCommon object (mundane items, foodstuff, cheap livestock, etc): 10\\nExpensive or masterwork object (incl rare spices and valuable materials): 15\\nRare object (incl raw ore, gems, and fine artwork): 20\\nExotic object (unusual gems, jewelry, fine art): 25\\nUnique object: 30','Fast appraisal (1 r): -5 (failure still allows non-fast retry)\\nAppropriate specialization: +4 circ\\nMagnifying glass: +2 circ\\nFor items valued by weight, a scale gives a +2 circumstance bonus.',NULL),(53,'Construct Item',1,'[Untrained, T10/20]','d20 + Crafting skill + Int mod vs. DC','Var','C, tools','1/3 of listed price','Tch','Instantaneous','One or more objects','You use this skill to craft one or more (non-magical) objects.','Every day you make a successful skill check, you produce a number of \"virtual\" sp equal to your skill check. When the sum reaches the object\'s listed price, the construction is finished.\\nIf you fail a check by 5 or more, 10% of the raw materials have been destroyed, increasing the cost accordingly.','Ver