the illusion is real.\\nF - The target disbelieves the illusion.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(172,'Shadow Jump',11,'[Su, Dark, Teleport]','d20 + Shadow Weave Affinity skill or Shadowdancing skill + Int mod + MAM vs. DC','6 AP','C','2 PP per sq distance','(2 x level) sq','Instantaneous','You','You transport yourself (and your carried belongings) instantly from one shadow to another within range.','S - You successfully jump to the desired shadow.\\nF - You fail to transport yourself between the shadows but can try again.','Shadow jump: 10',NULL,NULL),(173,'Enhance Mind Blade',11,'[Su]','(d20 + Soulknife skill + Wis mod + MAM)','5 AP','C','1 PP per PL','Personal','Mind blade\'s duration','One mind blade','You enhance a manifested mind blade with magic weapon powers corresponding to a PL of your skill level or less. You have to have the skills and skill levels listed as requirements for the enhancements.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(174,'Manifest Mind Blade',11,'[Su, MR, Boost]','(d20 + Soulknife skill + Wis mod + MAM)','5 AP','C','1 PP','Personal','Until dropped/dismissed','One mind blade','You create a semisolid blade of psionic energy. It is equivalent to a dagger or shortsword appropriate for your size, and it can be used to make any sort of melee attack (with normal skill bonuses according to the weapon).\\nThe mind blade can be damaged or broken and has DR 10 and 10 HP. If the blade is destroyed, dropped, or disarmed, it simply dissipates (but can be manifested again).\\nSpells and powers that enhance normal weapons can also be used on mind blades.\\nA mind blade gains an enhancement bonus to attack and damage equal to skill level divided by 4\\nSkill level 2: You can now throw a manifested mind blade (with a base range of 6 sq). A thrown mind blade dissipates after the attack, regardless of the result.\\nSkill level 5: The action time decreases to 3 AP. You can now create mind blades equivalent to longswords and bastard swords. You can have up to two mind blades manifested at a time (if you have two free hands).\\nSkill level 11: The action time decreases to 1 AP.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(175,'Psychic Strike',11,'[Su, MR, Boost]','(d20 + Soulknife skill + Wis mod + MAM)','5 AP','C','2 PP','Personal','Var','One mind blade','You infuse a manifested mind blade with additional energy. On the next successful strike, the mind blade causes 1d6 PP of damage in addition to its normal damage.\\nSkill level 8: The damage increases to 2d6 PP.\\nSkill level 13: You can substitute PP damage for ability damage to Int, Wis, or Cha. Each die of PP damage can be exchanged for one point of ability damage.\\nSkill level 16: The damage increases to 3d6 PP.\\nSkill level 24: The damage increases to 4d6 PP.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(176,'Identify Effect',11,'[Secret]','d20 + Spellcraft skill + Int mod + MAM vs. DC','Reaction or 5 AP','Vision',NULL,'Close (LoS)',NULL,'One effect','You try to identify a spell, psionic power, or other supernatural effect. If you are witnessing the effect as it is being activated (e.g. a spell being cast), the identification can be done as a reaction (0 AP cost).','S - You identify the aspect that you were looking for.\\nF - You fail to identify the effect and cannot try again on this effect until your skill improves.\\nCF - You misidentify the effect.','Identify type of effect (arcane, divine, psionic): 10 + PL\\nIdentify spell or power being cast: 15 + PL\\nDetermine the skill being used for the effect: 15 + PL\\nIdentify a spell or power in place: 20 + PL\\nIdentify magically shaped or created items: 20 + PL\\nIdentify spell or power from its effect on you: 25 + PL\\nIdentify strange or unique magical effect: 30+\\nDetect area of dead magic: 10 from inside the area, 20 from outside\\nDetect area of wild magic: 25 (3 rounds required to determine exact borders)','Effect of unknown skill: -5\\nEffect of known spell: +5\\nKnowledge (Arcana) synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls\\nKnowledge (Psionics) synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls\\nArcane, Divine, or Psi synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls',1),(177,'Identify Glyph',11,'[Secret]','d20 + Spellcraft skill + Int mod + MAM vs. DC','5 AP','Vision',NULL,'Close (LoS)',NULL,'One glyph or symbol','You try to identify the purpose and effect of a magical glyph or symbol.','S - You successfully identify the glyph.\\nF - You fail to identify the glyph and cannot try again until your skill improves.\\nCF - You misidentify the glyph.','Identify magical glyph: 10 + PL','Knowledge (Arcana) synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls',NULL),(178,'Learn Ritual',7,'[Su]','d20 + Spellcraft skill + Int mod vs. DC','8 h','C',NULL,'Tch',NULL,'One written ritual','You try to learn and understand an arcane or divine ritual, either from writing or a teacher.','S - You learn the ritual and can now try to perform it.\\nF - You fail to learn the ritual and cannot retry until your skill improves.','Learn a ritual: 15 + PL','Knowledge (Arcana) synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls\\nKnowledge (Psionics) synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls\\nArcane, Divine, or Psi synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls',NULL),(179,'Research Spell',7,'[Su]','d20 + Spellcraft skill + Int mod vs. DC','1 day per power level','C',NULL,'Tch',NULL,'One spell or power','You try to develop a spell or psionic power.','S - You successfully research the spell or power and can now try to perform it.\\nF - You fail to develop the spell or power and cannot retry until your skill improves.','Research a spell or power: 15 + PL','Knowledge (Arcana) synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls\\nKnowledge (Psionics) synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls\\nArcane, Divine, or Psi synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls',NULL),(180,'Spellfire Absorption',11,'[Su]','d20 + Spellfire skill + Con mod + PAM vs. 10 + PL','6 AP','C, S','See below','Tch','Instantaneous','One magical effect','You try to absorb the energy from an active spell or magic item. You use the energy to fuel your own body.\\nYou can (temporarily) absorb more than your normal SP total, but with the following side effects:\\n    Current SP <= Max SP: No special effect\\n    <= 120% of max: Eyes glow slightly. Physical contact with wielder releases 1d4 SP of spellfire.\\n    <= 140% of max: Skin tingles and eyes glow brightly. Physical contact releases 1d6 SP.\\n    <= 160% of max: Skin glows slightly and eyes brightly. Physical contact releases 1d8 SP.\\n    <= 180% of max: Skin glows and eyes are like lanterns. Physical contact releases 1d10 SP.\\n    <= 200% of max: Skin glows brightly and gives off heat. Physical contact releases 2d6 SP.\\n    > 200% of max: The wielder catches fire. All excess energy is released as damage to the wielder.\\nInvoluntary release of spellfire energy due to physical contact causes 3 HP of fire damage per SP.\\nA spellfire wielder with current SP above his normal maximum will automatically leak 1d6 SP per hour.\\nSkill level 4: You can now permanently drain magic items.\\nSkill level 6: This power can now be used as a readied action to absorb rays and targeted spells (but not area effects).','S - You successfully absorb the magical energy, regaining 1 SP per PL.\\nF - You fail to absorb the energy.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(181,'Crown of Fire',11,'[Su, MR, Boost, Fire]','(d20 + Spellfire skill + Con mod + PAM)','6 AP','C, S','20 SP/r','Personal','Ongoing (20 SP/r)','You','You surround yourself in a halo of white-hot flames. Any creature or weapon touching you takes 10d6 HP of fire damage, and you gain MR equal to 10 + skill level.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(182,'Spellfire Blast',11,'[Su, MR, Boost, Fire]','d20 + Area Attacks skill mod + Dex mod + PAM + AB vs. Ref','6 AP','C, S','2 SP per d6 damage\\n(up to (4 + skill level/4) SP)','0','Instantaneous','Line 12 sq long\\nor Conical burst, 8 sq long','You unleash a blast of silver-white fire.','S - The target takes the indicated amount of fire damage.\\nCS - The target takes double damage.\\nF - The target takes only half damage.\\nCF - The target avoids all damage.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(183,'Spellfire Bolt',11,'[Su, MR, Boost, Fire]','d20 + Ray Attacks skill mod + Dex mod + PAM + AB vs. DeC','6 AP','C, S','1 SP per d6 damage\\n(up to (4 + skill level/4) SP)','Long (LoE)','Instantaneous','Ray','You fire a bolt of arcane silver-white fire at a target within range.\\nSkill level 2: Spellfire energy can now be released in minute and controlled amounts. Lighting small fires, torches, lanterns, etc. can be done at 0 SP cost (maximum range: long).\\nSkill level 3: You can choose to fire two separate rays (dividing the damage equally).\\nSkill level 4: You can now angle the ray around corners (negating cover and good cover).\\nSkill level 5: You can choose to fire three separate rays (dividing the damage equally).\\nSkill level 6: The bolt can now be readied to knock thrown weapons and projectiles out of the air (successful attack roll is still required against each weapon).\\nSkill level 8: You can choose to fire four separate rays (dividing the damage equally).','S - You inflict the indicated amount of fire damage.\\nCS - The target takes double damage.\\nF - You hit with a glancing strike for half damage.\\nEF - You miss the intended target.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(184,'Spellfire Flight',11,'[Su, Fire]','(d20 + Spellfire skill + Con mod + PAM)','6 AP','C','5 SP/r','Personal','Ongoing (5 SP/r)','You','By projecting your spellfire towards the ground, you can fly at a base speed of 6 and average maneuverability.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(185,'Spellfire Healing',11,'[Su, MR, Boost, Radiant]','(d20 + Spellfire skill + Con mod + PAM)','9 AP','C, S','1 SP per HP of healing','Tch','Instantaneous','1 living creature','You use your spellfire energy to heal the target. You can use up to your skill level in SP, and each SP heals 1 HP.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(186,'Spellfire Shield',11,'[Su, MR, Boost, Fire]','(d20 + Spellfire skill + Con mod + PAM)','3 AP','C','2 SP/r','Personal','Ongoing (2 SP/r)','You','You protect yourself within an aura of silver-white spellfire. It can have one of the following effects (spellfire wielder\'s choice each round):\\n    Cold resistance equal to your skill level.\\n    Protection against detection, divination, and scrying (PL = skill level).\\n    Ability to breathe water.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(187,'Alter Appearance',11,'[Su]','(d20 + Wild Shape skill + Wis mod + PAM)','9 AP','C','1 SP','Personal','Permanent (D)','You','You assume a different form or appearance (but within your own creature type). This is a grade I shapechange.','S - You alter your appearance as desired.\\nF - You fail to alter your appearance but can try again.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(188,'Elemental Shape',11,'[Su]','(d20 + Wild Shape skill + Wis mod + PAM)','9 AP','C','20 SP','Personal','1 day (D)','You','You alter your shape into an elemental, according to the limitations given by your skill level. Except as noted above, this is a grade III shapechange.\\nSkill level 16: You can turn into small, medium, or large elementals.\\nSkill level 20: You can also turn into huge elementals.\\nSkill level 24: You can also turn into any elemental creature up to huge size.','S - You alter your shape successfully.\\nF - You fail to alter shape but can try again.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(189,'Wild Shape',11,'[Su]','(d20 + Wild Shape skill + Wis mod + PAM)','9 AP','C','10 SP','Personal','1 day (D)','You','You alter your shape into an animal or plant, according to the limitations given by your skill level.\\nIf you are wounded, you regain TL HP when returning to your natural form.\\nExcept as noted above, this is a grade II shapechange.\\nSkill level 3: You gain the ability to turn into any normal (and immobile) plant of small or medium size. While in plant form, you have your regular senses and abilities of observation, but you have Dex 0, base speed 0, and no ability to speak or cast spells with verbal, somatic, or material components.\\nSkill level 5: You gain the ability to turn into any animal of small or medium size. Most forms will only allow casting of spells without verbal, somatic, and material components.\\nSkill level 8: You can also turn into large animals and plants.\\nSkill level 11: You can also turn into tiny animals and plants.\\nSkill level 12: You can also turn into plant creatures.\\nSkill level 15: You can also turn into huge animals and plants.','S - You alter your shape successfully.\\nF - You fail to alter shape but can try again.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(190,'Control Transformation',12,'[Su, Untrained]','d20 + Lycanthropic Control skill + Wis mod + PAM vs. DC','Reaction or full round','C',NULL,'Personal','Instantaneous','You','You either try to resist an involuntary transformation or to trigger a voluntary one.\\nAs a lycanthrope, you may involuntarily change into your animal form. This happens during the nights of a full moon and every time you first take damage during a combat encounter. You are allowed a Control Transformation check to avoid changing shape. The shapechange is a grade II change.\\nSkill level 1: You are now able to attempt voluntary changes to your animal form and back to humanoid form.\\nSkill level 2: You are now able to attempt voluntary changes to and from a hybrid form. This too is a grade II shapechange. You still need to make checks to remember your actions and to avoid alignment change.\\nSkill level 5: You no longer need to make checks to remember your actions or avoid alignment change.\\nSkill level 8: The change of shape now takes 6 AP instead of a full round.','S - You manage to resist or trigger the transformation.\\nF - You fail to resist or trigger the change. If it is an involuntary change or a change to humanoid form, it takes 1 day before you can retry.','Resist involuntary change: 25\\nVoluntary change to humanoid form (full moon): 25\\nVoluntary change to humanoid form (not full moon): 20\\nVoluntary change to hybrid form: 15\\nVoluntary change to animal form (full moon): 15\\nVoluntary change to animal form (not full moon): 20',NULL,NULL),(191,'Gaze Attack',12,'[Su]','d20 + Body & Mind skill mod + PAM + AB vs. Fort','6 AP','C, vision',NULL,NULL