ck',6,'[Su]',NULL,'As per attack + 3 AP','As per weapon','+3 PP','As per weapon','One attack','As per weapon','Ghost Attack: When you are about to make a weapon attack (with a natural, melee, or ranged weapon), you can choose to spend 3 PP to infuse it with psionic energy. The attack will then cause normal damage against incorporeal targets.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(204,'Penetrating Attack',6,'[Su]',NULL,'As per attack + 3 AP','As per weapon','+3 PP','As per weapon','One attack','As per weapon','Penetrating Attack: When you are about to make a weapon attack (with a natural, melee, or ranged weapon), you can choose to spend 3 PP to infuse it with psionic energy. For this attack, halve the target\'s DR.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(205,'Aligned Attack',6,'[Su]',NULL,'As per attack + 3 AP','As per weapon','+3 PP','As per weapon','One attack','As per weapon','Aligned Attack: When you are about to make a weapon attack (with a natural, melee, or ranged weapon), you can choose to spend 3 PP to infuse it with psionic energy of a specific alignment (must match your own alignment, at least partially). The attack counts as an aligned attack of the appropriate type, with respect to aligned DR. Furthermore, with a successful hit, you deal an additional 1d6 HP of damage.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(206,'Psionic Power Attack',6,'[Su]',NULL,'As per attack + 3 AP','As per weapon','+3/6 PP','As per weapon','One attack','As per weapon','Psionic Power Attack: When you are about to make a weapon attack (with a natural, melee, or ranged weapon), you can choose to spend 3 PP to infuse it with psionic energy. With a successful hit, you deal an additional 2d6 HP of damage.\\nLvl 15 - Greater Power Attack: Same as Power Attack, but you can spend 6 PP to increase the damage by 4d6 HP.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(207,'Wounding Attack',6,'[Su]',NULL,'As per attack + 3 AP','As per weapon','+3 PP','As per weapon','One attack','As per weapon','Wounding Attack: When you are about to make a weapon attack (with a natural, melee, or ranged weapon), you can choose to spend 3 PP to infuse it with psionic energy. With a successful hit, you deal 1 point of Con damage (in addition to the normal weapon damage).',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(208,'Use Influence',10,'[Lang, Secret]','d20 + influence + Cha mod + other mods vs. DC or opposing Psychology (Sense Motive)','1+ min','V',NULL,'Close (LoH)','Instantaneous','Invidividual or organization','You exert your power over the target and request their help with something.','S - The target provides you with minimal aid.\\nCS - The target provides you with as much aid as they possibly can.\\nF - The target regretfully denies your request.\\nCF - The target becomes a new enemy.','Request shelter (small party): 12\\nGain access to news and gossip: 12\\nRequest lodging (large party or extended stay): 15\\nFresh supplies and horses (small party): 18\\nMedicines and treatment for wounded: 18\\nConfirm rights, legitimacy, or resolve minor dispute: 18\\nLend use of expert: 20\\nConfirm rights, legitimacy, or resolve significant dispute: 20\\nRequest protection from lesser authority: 25\\nConfirm rights, legitimacy, or resolve major dispute: 25\\nLend use of small company or several experts: 30\\nRequest protection from equal authority: 35\\nLend use of major military force: 35\\nRequest protection from greater authority: 40','Using group influence against individual target: -10\\nDifference in SC (social class): ยฑ4 per rank\\nTarget has family ties or sworn direct service to you: +5\\nTarget has friendly attitude: +5\\nTarget has hostile attitude: -5\\nPerform service for target: Varies\\nBribe, gift, or blackmail: Varies\\nDanger or inconvenience for target: Varies\\nApplicable reputation: +1/2 or -1/2 reputation value\\nHelpful influence from third party: +(Up to the third party\'s influence)\\nOpposing influence from third party: -(Up to the third party\'s influence)\\nClearing debt (works only on individuals): By permanently reducing your influence, y