Su]','Natural weapon attack vs. DeC','As per attack\\n-1 AP for non-damaging touch','C, natural weapon','As per attack','As per attack',NULL,'1 target','The familiar or psicrystal delivers a touch spell on behalf of its master. The familiar or psicrystal must be within 1 square of the caster at the time of casting.','S - The attack succeeds and the spell is delivered.\\nES - Halve DR and other resistances against this attack.\\nCS - Treat both the attack and the spell attack as a critical success.\\nF - The attack misses and the charge remains (until the master does something to drop concentration).',NULL,NULL,NULL),(271,'Shadow Cloak',12,'[Su, Dark]',NULL,'6 AP','C','5 PP','Personal','Ongoing (1 PP/r)','You','You wrap yourself in a cloak of magical darkness that grants concealment in normal light and good concealment in dim light.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(272,'Initiate Combat Telepathy',11,'[Su, Mind, Telepathy]','d20 + Combat Telepathy skill + Wis mod + MAM vs. DC','4 AP (once/r)','C','2 PP/r','Personal','Ongoing (2 PP/r)','You','You reach out with your telepathic abilities, trying to instinctively read the surface thoughts of nearby creatures. While paying the cost, you receive a +1 insight bonus to DeC and attack rolls against one thinking creature (Int 1 or higher) within 6 sq. You can select a new creature at the beginning of each of your turns.\\nSkill level 2: You can now gain the bonus against two creatures simultaneously.\\nSkill level 3: The insight bonus increases to +2.\\nSkill level 4: You can now gain the bonus against three creatures simultaneously.\\nSkill level 5: The insight bonus increases to +3.\\nSkill level 6: The ongoing cost decreases to 1 PP/r.\\nSkill level 7: The insight bonus increases to +4.\\nSkill level 8: You can now gain the bonus against four creatures simultaneously.\\nSkill level 9: The insight bonus increases to +5.\\nSkill level 10: You now gain the bonus against all thinking creatures within 6 sq.','S - You initiate combat telepathy and gain the indicated bonuses.\\nF - You fail to initiate combat telepathy. You can try again next round.','Initiate combat telepathy: 10',NULL,NULL),(273,'Antimagic Strike',11,'[Su]','Weapon attack vs DeC','As per attack + 3 AP','C, weapon','As per attack + 1 PP','As per attack','Instantaneous','1 creature','You enhance your attack with an infusion of mental power. If the attack succeeds, your weapon causes 1d6 PP of damage in addition to its normal damage.\\nSkill level 3 in Mind over Magic: The damage increases to 2d6 PP.\\nSkill level 8: You can substitute PP damage for ability damage to Int, Wis, or Cha. Each die of PP damage can be exchanged for one point of ability damage.','S - The weapon deals PP damage in addition to its normal damage.\\nCS - The attack causes double PP damage, in addition to its normal critical damage.\\nF - The attack misses.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(274,'Turn Spell',11,'[Su]',NULL,'Reaction',NULL,'10 PP','Spcl','Instantaneous','Spcl','When a supernatural targeted attack or ray fails against you, you can choose to pay the cost for this reaction and reflect the attack back upon the attacker. Note that this power does not automatically identify the incoming attack.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(275,'Detect Magic',11,'[Su]',NULL,'9 AP','C',NULL,NULL,'Concentration','Cone emanation 6 sq','You sense the presence of magical auras.','1st round - You detect the presence or absence of magic.\\n2nd round - You detect the number of magical auras and the power of the most potent one.\\n3rd round - You detect the power and location of each aura. You can make Spellcraft checks to further investigate and analyze each aura.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(276,'Heckle',10,'[Untrained, Lang]','d20 + Psychology (Influence) skill + Cha mod vs. opposing skill','1+ min','V',NULL,'Close (LoH)','Instantaneous','1 or more creatures','You heckle the target in an attempt to sabotage a performance or social action made by that creature.','S - The target is forced to reroll its performance or social skill check. For every 5 levels of success, the target suffers a -2 penalty on the check\\nF - The target gains a +2 bonus on subsequent checks. The heckling may not be retried for this particular action.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(277,'Mediate',10,'[Untrained, Lang]','d20 + Psychology (Influence) skill + Cha mod vs. DC or opposing skill','1 day','V',NULL,'Close (LoH)','Instantaneous','2 or more creatures','You try to mediate between two or more creatures and improve their attitudes towards one another.','S - You change the target\'s attitude towards another participant by one step. Further checks can be made.\\nCS - You change the target\'s attitude towards another participant by two steps. Further checks can be made.\\nF - You fail to change the target\'s attitude. Retrying is possible, if the situation permits.\\nCF - The target\'s attitude is changed in the opposite direction. If any target becomes hostile, the mediation has failed and can no longer be retried.','Initially unfriendly or indifferent target: 15\\nFriendly target: 20','Rushed attempt (1 hour): -10\\n1st level of language proficiency: -5\\n3rd level of language proficiency: +5\\nKnowledge (Nobility) synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls (if the target has a social class of 2 or more)',1),(278,'Challenging Stare',10,'[Untrained, Mind, Fear]','d20 + Psychology (Influence) skill + Cha mod vs. opposing skill check','1 r (once per enc)','Vision',NULL,'6 sq (LoS)','1 r or 1 enc','1 creature of Int 3+','In anticipation of a combat situation (but not once combat has begun), you can stare down an opponent and try to engage it in a duel of wills. ','When you use a challenging stare, the target has three options:\\nSubmit - If combat starts, the opponent suffers a morale penalty of -2 on initiative and -1 on attack rolls for 1 round.\\nIgnore - If your check beats DC 15 and combat starts, you gain a morale bonus of +1 on attack rolls against the target for 1 round.\\nParticipate - You and the target make opposed checks. If combat starts, the winner gains a morale bonus of +1 on attack rolls and damage rolls against the loser, while the loser suffers a -1 morale penalty on attack rolls and damage rolls against the winner.',NULL,'Difference in size: +/-4 per size category\\nBerserking synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls',1),(279,'Assess Opponent',10,'[Untrained, Secret]','d20 + Psychology (Insight) skill + Wis mod vs. opposing Psychology (Bluff)','6 AP','Vision',NULL,'6 sq (LoS)','Instantaneous','1 creature','You try to determine how challenging the target would be to face in a fight.','S - You find out if the target\'s CL is higher, the same, or lower than your own.\\nES - You can tell the target\'s CL (within an error margin of +/- 2)\\nF - You fail to make an assessment.\\nEF - You make a wrong assessment, believing the target to be much more or less challenging than it actually is.',NULL,'Seen the target in combat: +2',1),(280,'Taunt Opponent',10,'[Untrained, Mind, Secret]','d20 + Psychology (Influence) skill / 2 + Cha mod vs. Will','5 AP','V or S',NULL,'Close (LoH)','Var','1 creature','You try to taunt the target into attacking you (in preference to other targets).','S - The target attacks you, if doing so has no obvious disadvantages and there are no more tempting opponents.\\nES - The target tries to attack you in preference to other opponents for the rest of the encounter.\\nCS - The target tries to attack you with extreme prejudice (no DeB and no regard for its own safety).\\nF - The target ignores the taunt. Retrying against this target is not possible.',NULL,'Non-verbal taunt: -10',1),(281,'Bait Opponent',1,'[Secret]','d20 + Warfare skill + Wis mod vs. opposing Warfare or Combat Instincts skill check','3 AP',NULL,NULL,'Close (LoS)','Var','1 or more creatures','You use your positioning and stance to bait opponents into attacking you rather than other targets.','S - The targets attack you, if doing so has no obvious disadvantages and there are no more tempting opponents.\\nES - The targets try to attack you in preference to other opponents for the rest of the encounter.\\nF - The target acts normally. Retrying against this target is not possible.',NULL,NULL,1),(282,'Create Cipher',1,'[T10, Lang]','d20 + Linguistics skill + Int mod','1 week','C',NULL,NULL,NULL,'1 cipher','You create a cipher that can only be decoded by yourself, those that are provided with a proper key, and those that succeed on a Decipher Script check against a DC equal to 10 + this skill check.','See action description.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(283,'Tailing',1,'[Untrained, Secret]','Hide check vs. opposing Spot check','Var','C, vision',NULL,'LoS','Var','1 or more creatures','You try to follow someone by keeping them in sight while remaining unseen. The frequency of checks depends on the distance between you and your quarry; a recommended guideline is once per 10 minutes when the distance is above 12 sq, otherwise once per round.','S - You successfully follow your target.\\nF - The target notices you.\\nEF - The target notices you and shakes you off (or arranges an ambush).','See Hide and Spot actions for base difficulties.\\nTarget is worried about being followed: +10\\nTarget knows you by sight: +10','See Hide and Spot actions for base modifiers.\\nPerception synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls\\nPsychology synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls',1);
