INSERT INTO `spelloptions` VALUES (1,1,'Deafness',NULL,NULL,'+3 PP','You try to make the target deaf.'),(2,1,'Blindness',NULL,NULL,'+3 PP','You try to make the target blind.'),(3,1,'Disease',NULL,NULL,'+5 PP','Caster can choose one of the following diseases: Blinding sickness, Cackle fever, Filth fever, Mindfire, Red ache, Shakes, and Slimy doom. The disease strikes immediately, with no incubation period.'),(4,1,'Poison','[Poison]',NULL,'+5 PP','You inflict the target with a horrible poison (see Affliction Poison).'),(5,2,'Wind Walk',NULL,NULL,'+6 PP','The targets can also turn into gaseous form and back at will (5 r transformation time). When gaseous, a target can choose a base fly speed of 2 (perfect maneuverability) or 60 (poor maneuverability).'),(6,5,'Full Mobility',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','The objects gain full mobility and attack ability (see Animated Object in the creature chapter).'),(7,6,'Spike Growth',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','Instead of animating the plants in the area, you turn them into a mass of hard and sharp spikes. Their appearance does not change, but they cause 1d4 HP of damage for every square that a creature moves on foot through the area. Furthermore, if a +10 attack roll succeeds against a creature injured by the spikes, its movement is halved for 24 h (as per caltrop wounds).'),(8,6,'Liveoak',NULL,NULL,'+10 PP','You transform any Huge tree in the area into a treant-like creature (see the creature chapter) that defends you and obeys your spoken commands. If you pay +2 PP extra, you can transform any wooden staff or small tree into a full-sized treant.'),(9,6,'Full Mobility',NULL,NULL,'+7 PP for 1 plant\\n+12 PP for 2 plants\\n+20 PP for 4 plants','You give full mobility and attack ability to large plants in the area. A huge plant counts as two large and a gargantuan plant as four large. See Animated Objects in the creature chapter for details.'),(10,6,'Shambler',NULL,NULL,'+14 PP','You transform some of the undergrowth into 1d4+2 shambling mounds that defend you and obey your spoken commands.'),(11,7,'Anti-Vermin',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','The barrier also keeps out vermin (small mammals, insects, arachnids, etc).'),(12,7,'Anti-Animal',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','Like anti-vermin, but the barrier also keeps out animals and monstrous animals.'),(13,7,'Anti-Life',NULL,NULL,'+6 PP','Like anti-animal, but the barrier also keeps out aberrations, dragons, humanoids, and monstrous humanoids (but not outsiders, elementals, constructs, and undead).'),(14,8,'Magic Resistance',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP for specific\\n+8 PP for generic','Specific option: You grant the targets magic resistance equal to your skill level against all spells belonging to a single arcane, divine, or psi skill.\\nGeneric option: You grant the targets generic magic resistance equal to your skill level.\\nIf you select an emanation as the area of effect, you effectively create an area of anti-magic of the specified strength.'),(15,8,'Backlash',NULL,NULL,'+6 PP','Anyone who casts a spell or uses a power that can be affected by the Antimagic power suffers a backlash that inflicts a loss of 2 PP.'),(16,8,'Spell Turning',NULL,NULL,'+8 PP','You add spell turning to the protection. Casters who cast rays and targeted spells (but not area effects) against the resistance and fail will themselves become a target.'),(17,8,'Spell Leeching',NULL,NULL,'+8 PP','Same as spell turning option, but instead of turning a spell against its caster, you absorb some of the spell\'s power. If you are the target of a ray or targeted spell, and the spell fails, you gain half of the spell\'s PL as temporary PP.'),(18,10,'Location','[Scry]','Arcane - Divination','+2 PP','As long as you are in the same plane, you can sense the approximate direction and distance to the mark.'),(19,10,'Secret Chest','[Dimension]','Arcane - Conjuration and Ouranomancy','+8 PP','You mark a special chest (constructed of expensive materials and worth at least 500 gp) that you can repeatedly hide on the Ethereal Plane and summon to your present location at will (5 AP cost). Regardless of the chest\'s actual size, it can contain 30 litres per skill level.'),(20,10,'Summoning','[Teleport]','Arcane - Conjuration','+14 PP','If the mark is placed on an object weighing no more than 5 kg, you can summon it to your current location at any time (5 AP cost). If the object is held or carried by another creature, you have to make a spellcasting check against that creature\'s Will.'),(21,11,'Protection','[Illusion]',NULL,'+6 PP','When the ward triggers, a number of protective effects take place. The area fills with dense fog (as in Fog Cloud spell), all doors become magically held (as in Hold Object spell), stairways are filled with strong entangling webs, up to ten doors can be hidden behind illusory walls, and the fog can be made nauseating in two separate positions. All of these effects have a duration of one day.'),(22,12,'Shambler',NULL,NULL,'7 PP','Instead of an ectoplasmic creature, you create a pseudo-alive ectoplasmic mist. It has a size of 3x3 squares and is 2 squares in height, and it has a speed of 1. The mist is very thick and reduces visibility to one square. Furthermore, the mist is corrosive, and enveloped creatures take 5 HP of acid damage per round.'),(23,14,'Extendable (only for claws)',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','You can extend your claws greatly, increasing your reach by 1 square and making the claws count as one size larger.'),(24,14,'Pain Strike',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','Your natural weapons also cause 1d6 SP of damage with each successful attack.'),(25,14,'Graft Weapon (only for claws)',NULL,'Psi - Psychometabolism','+2 PP','Instead of turning your hands into beastly claws, you graft one or two one-handed weapons onto your hand or hands. A grafted weapon gains a +1 circumstance bonus to attack, parry, and damage, and it cannot be disarmed. However, a hand with a grafted weapon cannot be used as a regular hand (with the penalties this entails).'),(26,18,'Trigger Gem',NULL,NULL,'+2 PP','For this option, the material component has to be a single gem (instead of several). The spell is stored inside the gem and does not take effect until the intended target touches or picks up the gem.'),(27,18,'Sequester',NULL,'Arcane - Illusion','+4 PP','The target is also rendered invisible, and attempts to scry on or magically locate the target have to beat your spellcasting check.'),(28,19,'Anti-Force Weapon',NULL,NULL,'+6 PP','If the weapon strikes a [Force] effect of lower PL, that effect is dispelled.'),(29,19,'Wall of Blades',NULL,NULL,'+10 PP','Instead of a force shield or weapon, you create an immobile, vertical curtain of whirling blades of force up to 4 sq high (either a straight wall up to 4 x level sq long or a circular wall up to 1 x level sq diameter). Any creature standing in or crossing the wall is exposed to the indicated attack and suffers the effects. The wall provides cover in both directions.'),(30,23,'Shared Pain',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','This version does not reduce the damage you take. However, affected creatures take the same amount and type of physical damage (HP as well as SP) that you do for as long as the spell lasts. For example, if you take 10 HP of damage, all affected creatures also take the same damage.'),(31,23,'Ability Affinity',NULL,NULL,'+6 PP','In addition to HP and SP, affected creatures also suffer the same ability damage to physical ability scores (Str, Con, and Dex) as you do.'),(32,23,'Healing',NULL,NULL,'+8 PP','In addition to suffering the same damage, affected creatures enjoy the same healing of HP and SP as you. If this is combined with the ability affinity option, healing of ability damage will also affect all targets.'),(33,23,'Fate Link',NULL,NULL,'+8 PP','Instead of creating a one-way affinity from yourself to the targets, you create a mutual affinity between you and all the affected targets. Whenever one of the targets suffers some damage, all other targets take the same damage.'),(34,24,'Breath',NULL,NULL,'+4 PP','This option di