INSERT INTO `spells` VALUES (1,'Affliction','[Su, MR, AoO]','Arcane - Necromancy\\nDivine - Nature\\nDivine - Retribution','(Tch: d20 + Dex mod + Weapons - Natural skill mod + MAM + AB + others mods vs. DeC and then)\\nd20 + Con mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Fort','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','0 PP','Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)\\nMedium (+6; LoS)','Special (+0)','1 living creature (+0)\\n2 living creatures (+2)\\n3-4 living creatures (+4)\\n5-8 living creatures (+6)\\n9-16 living creatures (+8)','You afflict the targets with deafness, blindness, poison, and/or a debilitating disease (see options).','Disease option: Caster can choose one of the following diseases: Blinding sickness, Cackle fever, Filth fever, Mindfire, Red ache, Shakes, and Slimy doom. The disease strikes immediately, with no incubation period.\\nPoison option [Poison]: You inflict the target with a horrible poison (see Affliction Poison).','S - The target suffers the chosen effects for 1 round.\\nES - The target suffers the chosen effects for the rest of the encounter.\\nCS - The effect becomes permanent (does not apply to poison option).\\nF - The target avoids the effect.',NULL),(2,'Air Walk','[Su, MR, AoO, Air]','Divine - Elements',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nF (divine focus)','7 PP','Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)\\nMedium (+6; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)','1 creature (+0)\\n2 creatures (+2)\\n3-4 creatures (+4)\\n5-8 creatures (+6)\\n9-16 creatures (+8)','The targets can tread on air as if it was solid ground. They can walk up or down at a maximum angle of 45 degrees.\\nA mount of animal intelligence has to be trained before it can walk on air successfully.','Wind walk option: The targets can also turn into gaseous form and back at will (5 r transformation time). When gaseous, a target can choose a base speed of 2 (perfect maneuverability) or 60 (poor maneuverability).',NULL,NULL),(3,'Analyze Dweomer','[Su, AoO]','Arcane - Divination and Ouranomancy\\nPsi - Clairsentience (+2 PP cost)','(d20 + Wis mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Will)','1 h (+0)\\n1 min (+6)\\n9 AP (+10)\\n6 AP (+16)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nF (500+ sp gem)','1 PP','Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)\\nMedium (+6; LoS)','Instantaneous (+0)\\nConcentration (+4)','Objects or creatures (+0)','You discern all active spells and magical properties of an object or creature. If you choose the \"concentration\" duration, you can redirect the spell and analyze multiple targets (one per round).\\nFor magical items, you learn of all functions, how to activate them, and how many PP it has. For active spells, you learn of the skill, the spell, and the power level.',NULL,'S - You discern all active spells and magical properties of the target.\\nF - You fail to analyze the target.',NULL),(4,'Animal Shapes','[Su, MR, AoO]','Wild Shape',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','11 PP','Close (+0; LoS)','1 day (D; +0)','1 willing creat. (+0)\\n2 willing creat. (+2)\\n3-4 willing creat. (+4)\\n5-8 willing creat. (+6)\\n9-16 willing creat. (+8)','You change the shape of all targets into the same kind of animal. This is a grade II shapechange.\\nEach target can terminate the effect on itself at will.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(5,'Animate Objects','[Su, AoO]','Arcane - Transmutation\\nDivine - Life\\nPsi - Psychokinesis',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP','Medium (+0; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','1 small object (+0)\\n2 small objects (+2)\\n3-4 small objects (+5)\\n5-8 small objects (+10)\\n9-16 small objects (+18)','The basic spell allows you to give simple commands to inanimate and unattended objects (but within their inherent limitations). For example, a rope can be commanded to \"coil\", \"knot\" itself, \"loop\", \"uncoil\", \"entangle\" (a creature in the same square), etc. An unlocked chest can be commanded to \"open\" or \"close\".\\nLarger objects than small can also be animated. One medium object counts as two small, one large as four small, one huge as eight small, and one gargantuan as sixteen small.','Full mobility option: The objects gain full mobility and attack ability (see the creature chapter).',NULL,NULL),(6,'Animate Plants','[Su, AoO]','Divine - Plants',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP','Medium (+0; LoS)\\nLong (+3; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','Plants in spherical spread; 8 sq radius (+0)','The basic spell animates all normal plants in the area of effect and causes them to entangle all creatures that enter the area.','Spike growth option: Instead of animating the plants in the area, you turn them into a mass of hard and sharp spikes. Their appearance does not change, but they cause 1d4 HP of damage for every square that a creature moves on foot through the area. Furthermore, if a +10 attack roll succeeds against a creature injured by the spikes, its movement is halved for 24 h (as per caltrop wounds).\\nFull mobility option: You give full mobility and attack ability to a maximum of eight large plants in the area. A huge plant counts as two large, a gargantuan plant as four large, and a colossal plant as eight large. See animated objects in the creature chapter for details.\\nLiveoak option: You transform any Huge tree in the area into a treant-like creature (see the creature chapter) that defends you and obeys your spoken commands.\\nChangestaff option: Same as the liveoak option, but this instead transforms any wooden staff (or small tree).\\nShambler option: You transform some of the undergrowth into 1d4+2 shambling mounds that defend you and obey your spoken commands.',NULL,NULL),(7,'Antilife Shell','[Su, MR, AoO]','Divine - Protection',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nF (divine focus)','5 PP for anti-plant','0 (+0)','Ongoing (+0; 2 PP/h)','Spherical emanation; 2 sq radius (+0)','The basic spell creates an invisible and mobile barrier that keeps out plant creatures and animated plants.\\nForcing the barrier against an affected creature disrupts the field.','Anti-vermin option: The barrier also keeps out vermin (small mammals, insects, arachnids, etc).\\nAnti-animal option: Like anti-vermin, but the barrier also keeps out animals, monstrous animals, and vermin.\\nAnti-life option: Like anti-animal, but the barrier also keeps out aberrations, dragons, humanoids, and monstrous humanoids (but not outsiders, elementals, constructs, and undead).',NULL,NULL),(8,'Antimagic','[Su, MR, AoO]','Arcane - Ouranomancy and Abjuration\\nDivine - Protection\\nPsi - Psychokinesis and Telepathy',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)\\nReaction (+10)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP for +1 resistance\\n+3 PP per additional +1','Personal (+0)\\nTch (+3)\\nClose (+6; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','1 creature (+0)\\n2 creatures (+2)\\n3-4 creatures (+4)\\n5-8 creatures (+6)\\n9-16 creatures (+8)\\nSpherical emanation; 2 sq radius (+0), 4 sq rad (+4), 6 sq rad (+8)','The basic spell grants a resistance bonus to defenses against spells and other supernatural effects.','Specific MR option: You grant the targets magic resistance equal to your skill level against all spells belonging to a single arcane, divine, or psi skill.\\nGeneric MR option: You grant the targets generic magic resistance equal to your skill level.\\nBacklash option: Anyone who casts a spell or uses a power that can be affected by the Antimagic power suffers a backlash that inflicts a loss of 2 PP.\\nSpell turning option: You add spell turning to the protection. Casters who cast rays and targeted spells (but not area effects) against the resistance and fail will themselves become a target.\\nSpell leeching option: Same as spell turning option, but instead of turning a spell against its caster, you absorb some of the spell\'s power. If you are the target of a ray or targeted spell, and the spell fails, you gain half of the spell\'s (total PP cost + PP boost) as temporary PP.',NULL,NULL),(9,'Antipathy/Sympathy','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind]','Arcane - Enchantment','d20 + Cha mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Will','1 h (+0)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nM (gem worth 100+ gp)','15 PP','Close (+0; LoS)','1 day (D; +0)\\nPermanent (D; +4; 100 XP cost per PL)','Location or object; Up to 8 cubes per level','With the Antipathy effect you cause an object or location to repel creatures of a specific race or alignment.\\nWith the Sympathy effect you cause an object or location to attract creatures of a specific race or alignment.',NULL,'S - The spell works as intended.\\nAntipathy: Affected creatures are unable to enter or approach.\\nSympathy: Affected creatures feel an overpowering urge to stay in the area or touch the object.\\nF - The spell fails to attract or repel the target.\\nAntipathy: Intended creatures feel uncomfortable (shaken) within the area of effect.',NULL),(10,'Arcane Mark','[Su, MR, AoO]','Arcane - Illusion','(d20 + Dex mod + Weapons - Natural skill mod + MAM + AB + others mods vs. DeC)','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP\\n+1 PP for invisible mark','Tch (+0)','Permanent (+0)','One personal mark','You mark any object or surface with your personal rune or mark (up to six separate characters). The mark can be no larger than 30x30 cm. On a living creature, the mark disappears after roughly one month.\\nBy paying the additional cost, you can make the mark invisible (but still visible to anyone able to detect magic or invisibility).','Invisible option: The mark is invisible, but can be seen by anyone able to detect magic or invisibility.\\nLocation option (req Arcane - Divination): As long as you are in the same plane, you can sense the approximate direction and distance to the mark.\\nSecret chest option (req Arcane - Conjuration and Ouranomancy; [Dimension]): You mark a special chest (constructed of expensive materials and worth at least 500 gp) that you can repeatedly hide on the Ethereal Plane and summon to your present location at will (5 AP cost). Regardless of the chest\'s actual size, it can contain 30 litres per skill level.\\nSummoning option (req Arcane - Conjuration; [Teleport]): If the mark is placed on an object weighing no more than 5 kg, you can summon it to your current location at any time (5 AP cost). If the object is held or carried by another creature, you have to make a spellcasting check against that creature\'s Will.',NULL,NULL),(11,'Arcane Ward','[Su, AoO]','Arcane - Abjuration and Divination',NULL,'10 min (+0)\\n1 min (+2)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nF (tiny bell)','1 PP\\n+4 PP keeps out normal animals\\n+4 PP trigger on ethereal/incorporeal','Close (+0; PoE)','1 day (D; +0)\\nPermanent (D; +4; 100 XP cost per PL)','Spherical emanation; 4 sq radius (+0), 8 sq radius (+4)','You create a ward that triggers a mental or audible alarm every time a creature of tiny or larger size enters without saying the password.\\nMental alarm: If you are within 1 km, you hear a mental \"ping\". It wakes you up from normal sleep but does not interrupt your concentration.\\nAudible alarm: A bell-like sound is heard for 1 round within the warded area and up to 12 squares outside.','Animal option: Normal animals will not willingly enter the area.\\nEthereal option: The alarm will also trigger on incorporeal and extradimensional creatures.\\nProtection option [Illusion]: When the ward triggers, a number of protective effects take place. The area fills with dense fog (as in Fog Cloud spell), all doors become magically held (as in Hold Object spell), stairways are filled with strong entangling webs, up to ten doors can be hidden behind illusory walls, and the fog can be made nauseating in two separate positions. All of these effects have a duration of one day.',NULL,NULL),(12,'Astral Construct','[Su, AoO, Dimension]','Psi - Metacreativity',NULL,'1 r (+0)\\n9 AP (+4)\\n6 AP (+10)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','2 PP per CL','Close (+0; PoE)\\nMedium (+3; PoE)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','Astral construct(s) (+0)','You use ectoplasm to create one or more astral constructs of the chosen total CL. They appear at any spot you choose within range and can act immediately. They automatically protect you and attack your opponents, but you can direct them to perform other actions.\\nWhen the spell ends or the creatures die, they dissipate without a trace.','Shambler option: Instead of an ectoplasmic creature, you create a pseudo-alive ectoplasmic mist. It has a size of 3x3 squares and is 2 squares in height, and it has a speed of 1. The mist is very thick and reduces visibility to one square. Furthermore, the mist is corrosive, and enveloped creatures take 5 HP of acid damage per round.',NULL,NULL),(13,'Atonement','[Su, AoO]','Divine - Blessing',NULL,'1 h (+0)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nF (divine focus)','9 PP','Tch (+0)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 living creature (+0)','You remove the burden of acts and misdeeds that have angered the target\'s deity. The target must be truly repentant.\\nIf the acts were committed unwittingly or unwillingly, there is no additional cost. If the acts were deliberate, however, the caster must sacrifice a part of his soul (500 XP). It is also recommended that the subject performs some sort of quest to prove his dedication and remorse.\\nAtonement can be used for the following more specific purposes:\\n- Reverse magical alignment change (no XP cost).\\n- Restore class benefits (may involve XP cost).\\n- Change of alignment (no XP cost).',NULL,NULL,NULL),(14,'Attack of the Beast','[Su, AoO]','Arcane - Transmutation\\nDivine - Animals\\nPsi - Psychometabolism',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP for bite attack\\n1 PP for claw attacks\\n+4 PP per damage dice increase (up to four steps)','Personal (+0)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','You (+0)','The basic spell transforms either your mouth into a fanged maw or your hands into sharp claws. If you are medium-sized, a transformed bite causes 1d8 P HP of damage, and a transformed claw deals 1d4 S HP of damage.\\nYou can spend additional PP to increase the damage dice, 3 PP per step.','Extendable option (only for claws): You can extend your claws greatly, increasing your reach by 1 square and making the claws count as one size larger.\\nPain strike option: Your natural weapons also cause 1d6 SP of damage with each successful attack.\\nGraft weapon option (req Psi - Psychometabolism; only for claws): Instead of turning your hands into beastly claws, you graft one or two one-handed weapons onto your hand or hands. A grafted weapon gains a +1 circumstance bonus to attack, parry, and damage, and it cannot be disarmed. However, a hand with a grafted weapon cannot be used as a regular hand (with the penalties this entails).',NULL,NULL),(15,'Awaken Intelligence','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind]','Divine - Animals or Plants','d20 + Dex mod + Weapons - Natural skill mod + MAM + AB + others mods vs. DeC\\nand then d20 + Wis mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Will (or DC 20 for a tree)','1 day (+0)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','9 PP, 250 XP','Tch (+0)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 animal or tree (+0)','You awaken a tree or animal to humanlike sentience. The awakened subject becomes friendly towards you but has no special obligations or compulsions to help you. It automatically learns to speak your native language.\\nAn awakened animal receives 3d6 Intelligence, +1d3 Charisma, and +2 racial levels.\\nAn awakened tree becomes an \"animated object\" of the same size but also receives Intelligence, Wisdom, and Charisma scores of 3d6.',NULL,'S - You awaken the animal or tree and grant it intelligence.\\nF - The spell fails.',NULL),(16,'Banishment','[Su, MR, AoO]','Arcane - Conjuration\\nDivine - Summoning\\nPsi - Psychoportation','(Tch: d20 + Dex mod + Weapons - Natural skill mod + MAM + AB + others mods vs. DeC and then)\\nd20 + Wis mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Will','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nF (see below)','7 PP','Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 creature (+0)\\n2 creatures (+2)\\n3-4 creatures (+4)\\n5-8 creatures (+6)\\n9-16 creatures (+8)','You try to banish an extraplanar creature back to its home plane.\\nNote that some creatures may wish to return and will therefore be willing targets.',NULL,'S - The extraplanar creature is sent back to its home plane.\\nF - You fail to banish the creature.','For every focus hated or feared by the target: +2'),(17,'Bestow Power','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind]','Divine - Charm and Life\\nPsi - Telepathy',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','2 PP per 1 bestowed PP','Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 creature (+0)\\n2 creatures (+2)\\n3-4 creatures (+4)\\n5-8 creatures (+6)\\n9-16 creatures (+8)','You channel your mental energy into the target creature(s), using it to cure their mental fatigue. The base cost is 2 PP per 1 bestowed PP (same amount for each target).',NULL,NULL,NULL),(18,'Binding','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind]','Arcane - Enchantment','(Tch: d20 + Dex mod + Weapons - Natural skill mod + MAM + AB + others mods vs. DeC and then)\\nd20 + Cha mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Will','1 min (+0)\\n1 r (+6)\\n9 AP (+10)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nM (gems worth 500+ sp per target\'s TL; only for creatures and for duration longer than an encounter)','9 PP','Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\n1 year (D; +6)\\nPermanent (D; +8)','1 creature or object (+0)','This spell creates a magical restraint to bind and/or hide the target creature or object.\\nYou can specify any number of triggering conditions that can end the spell prematurely and release the target. If the DM deems the conditions reasonable, they provide a bonus to the attack check.\\nThe following binding types can be chosen:\\n- Chaining (req Arcane - Transmutation): The target is immobilized and confined in magical chains. The chains generate an Antipathy effect that affects all creatures other than the caster.\\n- Slumber: The target becomes comatose and does not age nor need to eat, drink, or breathe for the duration.\\n- Bound Slumber (req Arcane - Transmutation): A combination of Chaining and Slumber.\\n- Imprisonment (req Arcane - Ouranomancy): Same as Slumber, but the target is also imprisoned far beneath the surface of the earth.\\n- Hedged Prison (req Arcane - Ouranomancy): The target is transported to a confined area (e.g. a labyrinth) from which it cannot escape.\\n- Metamorphosis (req Arcane - Transmutation): The target\'s body (but not head) assumes a gaseous form, and the target is bound within a magical container. The target remains aware and can still speak, but it is unable to escape, attack, cast spells, and use other skills and abilities. It does not age nor require food, drink, and air for the duration. Breaking the container ends the spell.\\n- Minimus Containment: The target is shrunk to a size of 2 to 3 cm and bound within a magical container. It does not age nor require food, drink, and air for the duration. Breaking the container ends the spell.','Sequester option (req Arcane - Illusion): The target is also rendered invisible, and attempts to scry on or magically locate the target have to beat your spellcasting check.\\nTrigger gem option: For this option, the material component has to be a single gem (instead of several).