nded (permanent duration).\\nMedium DR option: The aura provides a +10 divine bonus to DR vs non-magical weapons.\\nGreater DR option: The aura provides a +15 divine bonus to DR vs non-magical weapons.',NULL,NULL),(79,'Divine Favor','[Su, MR, AoO]','Divine - Blessing',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nF (divine focus)','1 PP for +1 bonus\\n+4 PP per additional +1 (up to +5 total)\\n+4 PP per 5 temporary HP\\n+2 PP per +1 Str bonus (up to +6)','Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','You (+0)\\n1 creature (+2)\\n2 creatures (+4)\\n3-4 creatures (+6)\\n5-8 creatures (+8)\\n9-16 creatures (+10)','You infuse the targets with divine power.\\nThe targets gain the specified morale bonus to all attacks and weapon damage.\\nYou can also pay extra PP for temporary HP and/or an enhancement bonus to Strength.','Temporary HP option: The targets gain the specified amount of temporary HP.\\nStrength bonus option: The targets gain the specified enhancement bonus to Strength.\\nEnlargement option: The targets increase in size by one size category, with the appropriate adjustments.',NULL,NULL),(80,'Dominate Creature','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind, Charm]','Arcane - Enchantment\\nPsi - Telepathy\\nCleric Affinity - Tyranny Domain','d20 + Cha mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Will','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','7 PP','Close (+0; LoS)\\nMedium (+3; LoS)\\nLong (+6; LoS)','Special (+0)','1 person (+0)\\n1 creature (+4)\\n2 creatures (+6)\\n3-4 creatures (+8)\\n5-8 creatures (+10)\\n9-16 creatures (+12)','You can control the actions of affected creatures with simple mental commands (compelled condition) as long as they remain within range. Note that you do not automatically receive sensory input from the affected creature, nor can it communicate telepathically with you. However, by concentrating on the spell, the caster can receive full sensory input, as it is perceived and interpreted by the target.\\nAffected creatures attempt to carry out the command to the exclusion of all other activities (except those necessary for survival).\\nCommands to act against the target\'s nature require a new check against Will, with the modifiers below.',NULL,'S - The target is successfully compelled for 1 round.\\nES - The target is compelled for the rest of the encounter.\\nCS - The effect\'s duration increases to one day.\\nF - The target is unaffected.','Commands against target\'s nature: -2\\nSuicidal commands: -5'),(81,'Earthquake','[Su, AoO, Earth]','Arcane - Lithomancy\\nDivine - Elements',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','15 PP','Long (+0; PoE)','1 r (+0)','Circular spread (S); 16 sq rad (+0), 24 sq rad (+4)','You create an intense but localized and brief earthquake. Creatures in the affected area suffer a penalty on most actions (PAM and MAM) due to the violent motion.\\nIn caves and tunnels, the spell causes the roof to collapse (see cavein). A similar effect applies to cliffs and other potential landslides and avalanches.\\nOpen ground shakes violently and splits into multiple fissures. All grounded creatures must withstand a +5 attack against Ref (S - Fall prone). Creatures standing near a fissure (25% chance) suffer a +10 attack against Ref (S - Fall into the fissure). Creatures falling into a fissure have one round to get out before being crushed (20d6 HP damage).\\nSmall bodies of water drain away into the fissures and turn into muddy ground.\\nEach structure in the affected area takes 100 HP of structural damage (not reduced by DR).',NULL,NULL,NULL),(82,'Ectoplasmic Glob','[Su, MR, AoO]','Psi - Metacreativity','d20 + Int mod + Area Attack skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Ref','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP','Close (+0; LoS)\\nMedium (+3; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 10