y - Time Domain','(d20 + Int mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Fort)','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)\\nReaction (+10)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','Haste: 3 PP for +2 AP (+5 PP per additional +2 AP)\\nSlow: 3 PP for -2 AP (+5 PP per additional -2 AP)','Personal (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)','Encounter (+0)','1 creature (+0)\\n2 creatures (+2)\\n3-4 creatures (+4)\\n5-8 creatures (+6)\\n9-16 creatures (+8)','This spell causes time to flow faster or slower for the target creatures.\\nThe haste version gives the targets an enhancement bonus to their AP (and half that enhancement bonus to base speed). The bonus AP can be used as normal AP, for attack bonuses, defensive bonuses, or for additional actions (but not until the start of the target\'s next turn).\\nThe slow version gives the targets an enhancement penalty to their AP.',NULL,'S - The target suffers or enjoys the chosen effect (from the start of its next turn).\\nF - The target is unaffected.',NULL),(133,'Manipulate Writing','[Su, AoO]','Arcane - Divination and Transmutation',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP','Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)','Instantaneous (+0)\\n(Permanent for illusory script and suggestive script)','1-2 pages of text (+0)\\n3-8 pages of text (+2)\\n1 book (+4)','The basic spell can be used to either identify or erase written text, whether it is mundane or magical. This can include glyphs, symbols, sigils, and other text-based traps.\\nMundane text is automatically affected, but your spellcasting check must beat the PL of magical text.','Illusory script option (req Arcane - Illusion): You hide the actual writing behind an illusion of either unintelligible text or something else entirely. Only you and people designated by you at the time of casting can read the true text. If you spend an additional 2 PP, a successful dispelling of the illusion will also cause the real text to be erased.\\nSuggestion option (req Arcane - Enchantment): You embed a suggestion (e.g. close the book and leave, forget the book\'s existence, etc) in the text. Make a +PL attack against the reader\'s Will (S - target obeys the suggestion for 30 minutes).',NULL,NULL),(134,'Meld with Nature','[Su, MR, AoO]','Divine - Nature',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','3 PP for plant meld','Personal or Tch (+0)','Ongoing (+0; 1 PP/h)','You (+0)\\n+(1 to 4) creatures (+4)','The basic spell lets you meld yourself and up to 50 kg of carried possessions (and optionally 1 to 4 other willing creatures) into a living plant. The plant has to be large enough to contain your body in all three dimensions. Your body remains just below the surface of the plant, letting you hear sounds and sense vibrations from the outside, but rendering your other senses effectively useless. Furthermore, you do not need to (and are unable to) breathe while melded. You remain fully conscious and can even cast non-verbal spells on yourself.\\nAny damage that beats the plant\'s DR will cause the same damage to you, and if the plant is damaged so as to become smaller than you, you are automatically expelled from it. Any transmutation of the plant is also likely to expel you.','Stone meld option: Instead of melding with a plant, you meld with a mass of natural stone.\\nNature stride option [Teleport]: After melding with nature, you can teleport to a similar plant or mass of stone within 400 squares (or 600 m). This action costs 5 AP and can be done once per round.\\nGreater stride option [Teleport]: Same as nature stride, but you can teleport to any similar plant or stone on the same plane. When you do this, however, the spell ends automatically.',NULL,NULL),(135,'Metabolic Trance','[Su, AoO]','Psi - Psychometabolism',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','3 PP','Personal (+0)','Instantaneous/spcl (+0)','You (+0)','The basic spell provides you with sustenance (food and water) for one day.','Stasis option: You enter a trance so deep that even magic cannot detect that you are alive. However, you remain fully aware of your surroundings, and you can dismiss the trance at any time (although this takes 4 rounds). Your metabolism is almost nonexistent, and one year of stasis equals a single day for the purpose of aging, hunger, thirst, and breathing.\\nRegeneration option: You briefly increase your rate of metabolism, gaining regeneration (10 HP/SP per round) for 20 minutes.',NULL,NULL),(136,'Mind Blank','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind]','Arcane - Abjuration and Enchantment\\nPsi - Telepathy\\nCleric Affinity - Mentalism Domain',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)\\nReaction (+10)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP for +1\\n+2 PP per additional +1','Personal or Tch (+0)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','You (+0)\\n1 creature (+2)\\n2 creatures (+4)\\n3-4 creatures (+6)\\n5-8 creatures (+8)\\n9-16 creatures (+10)','By emptying and/or shielding your mind, you gain the indicated resistance bonus to Will defense.','Fortification option: In addition to the improved Will defense, the spell halves any damage to health points and ability scores suffered from mind-affecting spells.\\nImmunity option: Any mind-affecting spell or effect attempted against the target has to beat your spell\'s PL. The same applies to all attempts to magically locate or detect the target.',NULL,NULL),(137,'Mind Reading','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind, Telepathy]','Arcane - Divination and Enchantment\\nDivine - Charm and Insight\\nPsi - Telepathy','d20 + Cha mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Will','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP','Close (+0; LoS)','Concentration (+0)\\nEncounter (D; +2)\\nOngoing (+6; 1 PP/h)','1 creature (+0)\\n2 creatures (+2)\\n3-4 creatures (+4)\\n5-8 creatures (+6)\\n9-16 creatures (+8)','The basic spell lets you know the target\'s current emotions and also its attitude towards you.','Surface read option: By reading the surface thoughts of the target creatures, you gain a +10 enhancement bonus on Psychology-based skill checks against them.\\nProbe memory option: You can reach into a target\'s mind and examine its memories. Discovering a single piece of information takes a full round, and perusing the memory of an event takes half the time of the actual event. Each successful attack lets you probe one memory.\\nSkill leech option: You \"borrow\" a single skill (caster\'s choice) from the target. For the duration of the spell, you effectively have as many skill ranks in that skill as the target.','S - You successfully read the target\'s mind.\\nF - Target is unaffected.',NULL),(138,'Mind Seed','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind]','Psi - Telepathy','d20 + Dex mod + Weapons - Natural skill mod + MAM + AB + others mods vs. DeC\\nand then d20 + Cha mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Will','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\n3000 XP','15 PP','Tch (+0)','Instantaneous (spcl; +0)','1 person (+0)','You place a seed containing your full psyche into the subconscious mind of the target. The seed germinates over a period of one week, during which the target gradually takes on your mannerisms and eventually personality and alignment.\\nAfter a full week, the seed has effectively become a lesser mental duplicate of you (as you were at the time of casting but eight levels lower). At this time, the seed will start to fight the target\'s mind for control of the body. Use the rules for possession to determine the exact results. If the occupier becomes expelled, this means that the mind seed is defeated and dies.\\nNote that even when the mind seed is in control, you have no mental connection to or control over it. It has your personality, but it is a separate and fully independent creature.',NULL,'S - The target is successfully seeded.\\nF - The target is unaffected.',NULL),(139,'Necrotic Mantle','[Su, MR, AoO, Necrotic]','Arcane - Necromancy','d20 + Int mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Fort','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','5 PP','Medium (+0; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','1 creature (+0)\\n2 creatures (+2)\\n3-4 creatures (+4)\\n5-8 creatures (+6)\\n9-16 creatures (+8)','The affected targets do not regain HP, SP, PP, or ability damage for the duration of the spell. This applies to natural healing as well as magical.',NULL,'S - The target cannot regain HP, SP, PP, or ability damage.\\nF - The target cannot regain HP, SP, PP, or ability damage for 1 round.\\nOF - The target is unaffected.',NULL),(140,'Petrification','[Su, MR, AoO, Earth]','Arcane - Lithomancy and Transmutation\\nPsi - Metacreativity and Psychometabolism','d20 + Con mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Fort','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','7 PP','Close (+0; LoS)\\nMedium (+3; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nPermanent (D; +4)\\nInstantaneous (+8)','1 creature/statue (+0)','Flesh to stone: Effectively petrifies the target creature (and all of its equipment). A creature transformed to stone becomes inert and non-living but does not really die; when the duration expires or the target is turned back to flesh in some other way, the creature is fully restored to its former state.\\nStone to flesh: Restores a petrified creature to normal. This can also be used to turn a man-sized mass of stone into inert (but edible) flesh.',NULL,'S - The target is paralyzed for 1 round.\\nES - The target is turned to stone or vice versa for the spell\'s duration.\\nF - The target is slowed (-2 AP and -2 speed) for 1 round.\\nOF - The target is unaffected.',NULL),(141,'Phase Door','[Su, AoO, Dimension]','Arcane - Ouranomancy\\nPsi - Psychoportation',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','9 PP for up to 2 sq depth\\n+3 PP per additional sq\\n+4 PP for private door','Tch (+0)','Ongoing (+0; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','1 x 1.5 sq opening','You temporarily \"phase out\" solid wood, plaster, or stone to create a passage. It does not work on metal walls, constructs, or living materials. Creatures still in the passage when the spell ends are shunted towards the nearest exit.\\nIf you pay the extra cost for a \"private door\", the passage is only visible and accessible to you and creatures designated by you. Certain detection powers can reveal the passage but do not provide access to it.','Private option: The passage is only visible and accessible to you and creatures designated by you. Certain detection powers can reveal the passage but do not provide access to it.',NULL,NULL),(142,'Planar Binding','[Su, MR, AoO]','Arcane - Conjuration\\nDivine - Summoning','d20 + Con mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Will (if target is unwilling)','10 min (+0)\\n1 min (+4)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','11 PP\\n30 XP per creature TL','Close (+0; LoS)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 extraplanar creat. (+0)','You call an extraplanar creature (either a specific individual or a type of creature) into your presence and try to bind it inside a magical circle. If the creature is unwilling, your attack must beat the target\'s Will. If the creature\'s TL exceeds your skill level, it can decide freely whether to answer your call or not, and it cannot be forcibly contained within the circle.\\nIf successfully contained, the creature is unable to leave, reach outside, or make attacks outside the circle. If the magical circle is broken or disturbed somehow, the creature is instantly released and is free to attack the caster or return to its home plane. Note, however, that the creature itself is unable to directly or indirectly disturb the circle.\\nOnce called, you can try to coerce or bargain with the creature to provide you with information, to fight for you, or to perform a service. The creature can be contained for a maximum of 1 day per skill level. Note that a divine caster who serves the same deity as a called extraplanar creature will be much more likely to elicit a helpful response or at least a fair bargain.\\nWhen the service and any subsequent transaction have been completed, the creature is released and returned to its own plane.',NULL,'S - You call and bind the extraplanar creature.\\nF - You successfully call the creature but fail to contain it.\\nCS - The summoned creature helps you willingly.\\nOF - The target creature fails to appear.','Spellcraft synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls'),(143,'Planar Projection','[Su, MR, AoO, Dimension, Teleport]','Arcane - Ouranomancy\\nDivine - Summoning\\nPsi - Psychoportation',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nM (gem worth 100+ gp)','15 PP for Astral Plane\\n+4 PP for Outer Plane\\n+4 PP for specific loc.','Personal (+0)\\nTch (+2)','Permanent (D; +0)','You or 1 willing creature (+0)\\n2 willing creatures (+2)\\n3-4 willing creatures (+4)\\n5-8 willing creatures (+6)\\n9-16 willing creatures (+8)','You project your soul (and those of the other targets) into the Astral Plane. Once there, the soul will typically create an astral body around itself.\\nYour point of arrival is essentially random.\\nYour physical bodies are helpless and in suspended animation while you are projecting.\\nAn incorporeal silvery cord connects your soul with your physical body, and if this cord should be broken, you die (astrally as well as physically).\\nEach participant can return to his body at will (and terminate the spell for him).\\nPaying for \"Outer Plane\" lets you project the souls all the way into an Outer Plane.\\nIf you pay for \"specific location\", you can specify a desired point of arrival in the destination plane.','Outer Plane option: You project the souls all the way into an Outer Plane.\\nSpecific location option: You can specify a desired point of arrival in the destination plane.',NULL,NULL),(144,'Planar Travel','[Su, MR, AoO, Dimension, Teleport]','Arcane - Ouranomancy\\nDivine - Summoning\\nPsi - Psychoportation',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nF (tuning fork)','9 PP for Ethereal\\n+2 PP for Shadowfell, Feywild, or Elemental Plane\\n+4 PP for alternate Prime\\n+4 PP precision location','Personal (+0)\\nTch (+2)','Instantaneous (+0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)','You or 1 willing creature (+0)\\n2 willing creatures (+2)\\n3-4 willing creatures (+4)\\n5-8 willing creatures (+6)\\n9-16 willing creatures (+8)','You travel physically to a different plane or dimension. If you travel between the Prime Material, Ethereal, Shadowfell, or Feywild planes (those that overlap the Prime Material), you appear in a location that matches your starting location. If you travel to a non-overlapping plane, you appear 5d% km from your desired location.\\nThe illusory and quasi-real nature of Shadowfell and Feywild lets you travel ten times as fast as normal (relative to the Prime Material). These planes can therefore be used to speed travel to a Prime Material destination.\\nFocus: Each plane requires a tuning fork of a specific material and tuned to a specific frequency.\\nBy paying for \"precision location\", you appear much closer (5d% m) to your desired destination.','Precision location option: You appear much closer (5d% m) to your desired destination.',NULL,NULL),(145,'Power Word','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind]','Arcane - Enchantment','d20 + Cha mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Will','6 AP (+0)\\n3 AP (+6)','V (+0)','13 PP for blindness\\n15 PP for stun\\n17 PP for death','Close (+0; LoS)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 creature (+0)','You utter a single word of power that assaults the mind of your target. The target does not actually have to hear the word in order to be affected.\\nThe blindness option causes permanent blindness.\\nThe stun option stuns the target for the rest of the encounter.\\nThe death option simply wills the target to death.',NULL,'S - The target is affected for 1 round (death effect causes paralysis).\\nES - You successfully affect the target for the specified duration.\\nF - You fail to affect the target.',NULL),(146,'Prismatic Attack','[Su, MR, AoO, Light]','Arcane - Illumination','d20 + Dex mod + Area Attack skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Ref','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','13 PP','0 (+0)','Instantaneous (+0)','Conical burst; 12 sq (+0)','You shoot a spray of vividly colored beams of light from your hand. One or two beams (roll d8) will strike each creature in the area, causing the effects described below.\\n1 - Red: 40 (or 20) HP of fire damage\\n2 - Orange: 60 (or 30) HP of acid damage\\n3 - Yellow: 100 (or 50) HP of electricity damage\\n4 - Green: Poison causing 3d6 (or 1d6) Con damage\\n5 - Blue: Petrification (or -5 AP penalty) for rest of encounter\\n6 - Indigo: Insanity (or 1d6 Wis damage)\\n7 - Violet: Sent to another plane (or no effect)\\n8: Struck by two random beams',NULL,'S - The target is blinded for 1 round and suffers the reduced effect described above.\\nES - The creature in question is blinded for the rest of the encounter and suffers full effect.\\nCS - The target suffers double damage.\\nF - The creature is dazzled for 1 round.\\nCF - The creature is unaffected.',NULL),(147,'Prismatic Barrier','[Su, MR, AoO, Light]','Arcane - Illumination',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','15 PP','0 (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoE)','Ongoing (+0; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +4; 100 XP cost per PL)','Vertical wall 1 x level sq long and 3 sq high (+0)\\nSpherical wall 4 sq diameter (+2)','You create an immobile and opaque barrier of multicolored light. It must be continuous and unbroken when formed. The wall actually consists of seven separate layers, each with its own protective power, damaging effect, and vulnerability. Effects and objects passing through the barrier are automatically stopped if the appropriate layer is still active. Creatures other than you that try to pass through the barrier suffer the damaging effects of all active layers. Each layer can be automatically negated by the vulnerabilities listed below, but the layers have to be removed in the indicated order.\\nOrder and color: Protection; Damaging effect; Vulnerability\\n1 - Red: Nonmagical ranged weapons; +20 vs Ref (40 or 20 HP of fire damage); Extreme cold\\n2 - Orange: Magical ranged weapons; +20 vs Ref (60 or 30 HP of acid damage); Extreme wind\\n3 - Yellow: Poison, gas, and petrification; +20 vs Ref (100 or 50 HP of electricity damage); Disintegrate\\n4 - Green: Breath weapons; +20 vs Fort (poison - 3d6 or 1d6 Con damage); Phase door\\n5 - Blue: Divination and mental attacks; +20 vs Fort (petrification); Force damage\\n6 - Indigo: All supernatural attacks; +20 vs Will (insanity); Bright light\\n7 - Violet: All objects and effects; +20 vs Will (sent to another plane); Antimagic',NULL,NULL,NULL),(148,'Produce Flame','[Su, MR, AoO, Fire]','Divine - Elements\\nKi - Study of Fire',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP\\n+2 PP per +1 damage','0 (+0)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)','Small flame (+0)','You create a flame as bright as a torch in your hand. The flame does not harm you or your equipment, but it can be used as a melee or thrown weapon (counts as tiny object; base range of 5 squares; can use Weapons - Natural, Weapons - Light Blades, or Weapons - Small Thrown for bonuses). The flame adds 1d6 HP of fire damage to your hand attacks (or causes just 1d6 HP of fire damage when thrown). Whenever you use the flame as a thrown weapon, a new flame appears in your hand.\\nNote that a flaming hand can hold and use other weapons, but attacks with those weapons do not gain any bonuses from the flame.','Flame blade option: The flame extends 1 m from your hand, increasing the fire damage to 1d10 HP and counting as a small-sized object (use Weapons - Natural or Weapons - Heavy Blades for bonuses).',NULL,NULL),(149,'Protection from Divination','[Su, MR, AoO]','Arcane - Abjuration and Divination\\nPsi - Clairsentience and Telepathy\\nMind over Magic',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)\\nReaction (+10)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP','0 or Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)','1 day (D; +0)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','You (+0)\\n1 creature/object (+2)','The basic spell grants a +10 circumstance bonus to Bluff checks and a +4 circumstance bonus to defenses against mind reading.','Lesser protection option: The spell also protects the target against any divination effect that detects auras. Any such attempt has to beat your spell\'s PL or reveal nothing.\\nImproved protection option: The spell protects against all divination effects, not just aura detection.\\nFalse aura option: Instead of preventing the target\'s aura from being detected, you hide it behind a false aura. You can choose the specifics of the false aura, including alignment, magic, life force, etc.',NULL,NULL),(150,'Protection from Scrying','[Su, MR, AoO]','Arcane - Abjuration and Divination\\nPsi - Clairsentience',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nM (25 sp of diamond dust per PL)','3 PP','0 or Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)','1 day (D; +0)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','You (+0)\\n1 creature/object (+2)\\nSpherical emanation; 8 sq rad (+6), 12 sq rad (+10), 16 sq rad (+14)','You protect a creature, object, or area against scrying. Any attempt at scrying has to beat your spell\'s PL or fail. If you choose range 0, the area is centered on and moves with you.','Detection option: You automatically detect any scrying against the target or within the area. If your spell\'s PL beats the spellcasting check of the scryer, you get a visual image of the scryer as well as his approximate direction and distance.\\nPrivacy option: The target area is also protected against direct observers and eavesdroppers. Anyone watching from outside sees only a foggy mass, and no sounds can escape from the inside to the outside. Those inside can see and hear normally.\\nFalse vision option (req Arcane - Illusion): You create a false image that will be seen (and heard) by any scryers unable to beat your spell\'s PL. You can concentrate to change the image at any time, but it otherwise remains static. If you combine this option with the privacy option, the same illusion can be presented to direct observers (instead of the fog).\\nBacklash option: Scryers who fail to beat the spell\'s PL also take 8d6 PP of damage.',NULL,NULL),(151,'Psychic Chirurgery','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind]','Arcane - Enchantment and Transmutation\\nPsi - Telepathy','(d20 + Dex mod + Weapons - Natural skill mod + MAM + AB + others mods vs. DeC)\\nand then d20 + Int mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Will','1 min (+0)\\n1 r (+6)\\n9 AP (+10)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','9 PP for modify memory','Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)','Instantaneous/spcl (+0)','1 living creature (+0)','You can modify a target\'s memories. This can be used to eliminate memories of an event, allow the target to perfectly recall an event, change the details of an event, or implant a memory of an event that never took place. Each modification takes as much time as the actual event.','Memory drain option: Instead of altering specific memories, you remove the benefits of recent experiences from the target creature. It gains two negative levels.\\nSkill deletion option: You can actually make the target forget a single skill, effectively reducing the level in that skill to 0. The only way to regain the skill is to relearn it or to use this spell again to undo the damage.\\nRestoration option: You cure the target of any mental illness, including mind-affecting spells and powers. This can also restore memories and skills lost to this spell or other instantaneous effects. You can also choose to restore all ability damage to mental ability scores and any negative levels the target is suffering from.','S - You successfully affect the target.\\nF - You fail to affect the target.',NULL),(152,'Regeneration','[Su, MR, AoO]','Divine - Life',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','3 PP\\n+2 PP for SP regeneration\\n+4 PP for PP regeneration','Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)','1 day (D; +0)','1 living creature (+0)\\n2 living creatures (+2)\\n3-4 living creatures (+4)\\n5-8 living creatures (+6)\\n9-16 living creatures (+8)','The targets\' natural rate of healing increases. Each hour, they regain HP as if one day had passed (at the appropriate level of activity).\\nSP regeneration: Targets also recover SP faster than normal, regaining SP every 5 minutes as if 1 hour had passed.\\nPP regeneration: Targets also recover PP faster than normal, regaining PP every 5 minutes as if 1 hour had passed.','SP regeneration option: Targets also recover fatigue faster than normal, 1 SP per level (TL) every 5 minutes.\\nPP regeneration option: Targets also recover power faster than normal, 1 PP per level (TL) every 5 minutes.',NULL,NULL),(153,'Reincarnate','[Su, AoO]','Divine - Animals and Life','Spellcasting check vs. base DC 20','10 min (+0)\\n1 min (+4)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nM (100 gp of rare oils)\\nF (divine focus)','11 PP','Tch (+0)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 corpse (+0)','You restore life to a creature that has been dead for a maximum of one day per skill level. You bring back its soul into a different body, randomly chosen by the spirits of nature. The creature\'s soul must be free and willing to return. Creatures that have been turned into undead, killed by necrotic damage, or died of old age incur a penalty on the spellcasting check (see Resurrection in Core Mechanics).\\nYou need at least a small part of the dead creature\'s body to use as a focus. The creature\'s soul will enter the body of a recently dead creature of a suitable type, as chosen by the spirits of nature. The new body will be healed of injuries and afflictions. The creature typically wakes up 2d10 km from the casting\'s location, but it will be able to sense the direction to that location.\\nThe race of the new body depends mainly on the predominant races in the vicinity. For a medium-sized humanoid, this is a suitable selection:\\n01 - Bugbear\\n02-13 - Dwarf\\n14-25 - Elf\\n26 - Gnoll\\n27-38 - Gnome\\n39-42 - Goblin\\n43-52 - Half-elf\\n53-62 - Half-orc\\n63-74 - Halfling\\n75-89 - Human\\n90-93 - Kobold\\n94 - Lizardfolk\\n95-98 - Orc\\n99 - Troglodyte\\n00 - Original body\\nRoll randomly for the new body\'s age and age category (01-25 juvenile, 26-75 adult, 76-00 mature). Determine the creature\'s new ability scores, base speed, racial bonuses, etc. as if this was a grade II shapechange.\\nBeing reincarnated is quite a traumatic experience and typically involves some memory loss (see the generic resurrection rules for exact amount of XP lost).',NULL,NULL,NULL),(154,'Repair Object','[Su, AoO]','Arcane - Transmutation\\nDivine - Elements\\nPsi - Metacreativity',NULL,'1 min (+0)\\n1 r (+4)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP\\n+2 PP for greater repair','Close (+0; LoS)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 object (+0)','You repair small breaks and tears in a single object (damage of less than half total HP). It can mend broken magical items but will not restore magic lost due to breakage.\\nThe basic spell can repair an object weighing up to 10 kg per skill level.\\nA partially damaged construct (that falls within the weight limit) can be repaired with this spell.\\nGreater repair: You can repair objects that have been severely damaged or crushed (any amount of HP damage). The weight limit increases to 100 kg per skill level.','Greater repair option: You can repair objects that have been severely damaged or crushed (any amount of HP damage). The weight limit increases to 100 kg per skill level.\\nFabricate option: You convert raw materials into a finished product. For example, you can turn trees into a bridge, hemp into a rope, wool into clothes, etc. The weight limit of the finished product is 100 kg per skill level.',NULL,NULL),(155,'Repel Objects','[Su, MR, AoO]','Divine - Elements and Protection',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','11 PP\\n+0 PP for wood\\n+2 PP for stone\\n+4 PP for metal','0 (+0)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','12 sq line-shaped emanation (+0)','You set up waves of energy that push away the chosen type(s) of matter. Once the spell has been cast, the path is stationary and does not move with you.\\nObjects weighing up to 250 kg move down the path at a speed of 8 squares per round. Small (<10 cm diameter), fixed objects break or bend, while larger, fixed objects remain unaffected. Creatures holding or carrying affected objects will be pushed along, unless they drop the items (or they are strong or heavy enough to resist).',NULL,NULL,NULL),(156,'Resize Animal','[Su, MR, AoO]','Arcane - Transmutation\\nDivine - Animals','d20 + Con mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Fort','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','3 PP for shrink\\n5 PP for growth\\n3 PP for giant vermin','Close (+0; LoS)\\nMedium (+3; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','1 animal (+0)\\n2 animals (+2)\\n3-4 animals (+4)\\n5-8 animals (+6)\\n9-16 animals (+8)','You decrease or increase the size of the target animals by one step. See the size alteration table for effects on Strength, Constitution, Dexterity, and natural DR.\\nWith the giant vermin variety, you turn normal insects, centipedes, spiders, or scorpions into their giant version (M-sized). You can increase their size further, up to colossal size, by spending 4 extra PP per size category.','Protection option: Targets also receive DR +10 vs non-magical weapons and a +3 resistance bonus on Fort, Ref, and Will defenses.','S - You can change the target\'s size.\\nF - The target resists.',NULL),(157,'Resize Object','[Su, AoO]','Arcane - Transmutation',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','5 PP','Tch (+0)','Ongoing (+0; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +4; 100 XP cost per PL)','1 object (+0)','This spell lets you shrink one nonmagical object, reducing its size to 1/16th in each dimension and reducing its volume and mass to 1/4000th. This is equivalent to a reduction in size of four categories.','Transmutation option: You also transmute the object to a cloth-like substance, and this will effectively suspend time for the object. For example, this application could be used on a burning torch or a bucket of water. If the cloth-like object is thrown against a solid surface, the spell ends, and the object reverts to normal.',NULL,NULL),(158,'Resize Creature','[Su, MR, AoO]','Arcane - Transmutation\\nPsi - Psychometabolism (target you only)','(d20 + Con mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Fort)','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP\\n+6 PP for true resize\\n+16 PP for greater resize','Close (+0; LoS)\\nMedium (+3; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','1 person (+0)\\n1 creature (+4)\\n2 creatures (+6)\\n3-4 creatures (+8)\\n5-8 creatures (+10)\\n9-16 creatures (+12)','You decrease or increase the size of the targets (and their equipment) by approximately 30%, doubling or halving their weight. Size increase results in a +2 size bonus to Strength and -1 size penalty to Dexterity, while a size decrease results in -2 size penalty to Str and +1 size bonus to Dex.\\nEquipment that leaves the target\'s possession immediately returns to its normal size.\\nTrue resize: You alter the target\'s size to double or half normal size (one full step in the size categories). See the size alteration table for effects on Strength, Constitution, Dexterity, and natural DR.\\nGreater resize: You can increase or decrease the size of the targets by two steps instead of one.','True resize option: You alter the target\'s size to double or half normal size (one full step in the size categories). See the size alteration table for effects on Strength, Constitution, Dexterity, and natural DR.\\nGreater resize option: You can increase or decrease the size of the targets by two steps instead of one.','S - You can change the target\'s size.\\nF - The target resists.',NULL),(159,'Resurrection','[Su, AoO, Radiant]','Divine - Blessing and Life','Spellcasting check vs. base DC 20','10 min (+0)\\n1 min (+4)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nM (1000 gp of diamonds)\\nF (divine focus)','13 PP\\n+4 PP for greater resurrection','Tch (+0)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 corpse (+0)','You restore life to a creature that has been dead for a maximum of one day per skill level. The creature\'s soul must be free and willing to return. Creatures that have been turned into undead, killed by necrotic damage, or died of old age incur a penalty on the spellcasting check (see Resurrection in Core Mechanics). Apply a further penalty of -10, if the spell is not cast on the plane where death occurred.\\nBeing resurrected is quite a traumatic experience and typically involves some memory loss (see the generic resurrection rules for exact amount of XP lost).\\nThe resurrection spell heals the target\'s body of any fatal injuries (as well as non-magical poison and disease), but the creature still wakes up severely weakened (set current HP, SP, and PP equal to the creature\'s TL). Missing body parts are not restored. Any ability damaged to 0 is restored to 1.\\nGreater resurrection: You can restore life to a creature that has been dead for up to 10 years per skill level. You also halve the check penalty for targets turned undead, killed by necrotic damage, or killed on another plane. All you need is some portion of the creature\'s body. The creature wakes up with full HP, SP, and PP, but still loses XP.','Greater resurrection option: You can restore life to a creature that has been dead for up to 10 years per skill level. You also halve the DC increase for targets turned undead, killed by necrotic damage, or killed on another plane. All you need is some portion of the creature\'s body. The creature wakes up with full HP, SP, and PP, but still loses XP.',NULL,NULL),(160,'Sanctuary','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind]','Arcane - Abjuration and Enchantment\\nDivine - Charm and Protection\\nPsi - Telepathy',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP','Personal or Tch (+0)','Encounter (D; +0)','You (+0)\\n1 creature (+4)','This spell protects the target creature against hostile attacks by mentally repelling attackers. Compare (10 + the spell\'s PL) against the Will of anyone attempting a direct attack (including ranged attacks and targeted spells but not including area attacks). If the spell wins, that attacker cannot make direct attacks against the protected creature for the duration of the spell.\\nIf the protected creature performs a hostile action against anyone, the spell ends.','Repulsion option: In addition to being protected against attacks, the target creature emanates a field that prevents hostile creatures from approaching. The field does not push creatures away, but it prevents affected attackers from moving closer to the target. The caster can set the radius of the emanation from 2 squares to 30 squares.',NULL,NULL),(161,'Scrying','[Su, AoO, Scry]','Arcane - Divination\\nDivine - Insight\\nPsi - Clairsentience','d20 + Wis mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. DC or Will (when scrying on a sentient creature)','1 h (+0)\\n10 min (+4)\\n1 r (+8)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','5 PP\\n+2 PP for hearing\\n+4 PP for magical senses','Long (+0)\\nUnlimited (+3)\\nExtraplanar (+6)','Concentration (+0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)','Magical sensor(s) (+0)','You create an invisible magical sensor (SZ Fine; 1 HP; DeC 18; Stealth +16) that sends you visual information from its vicinity (24 squares in all directions). The starting point must be within range and either known to you or within line of sight. You can also try to scry on an individual, but then you have to beat his Will defense.\\nYou can use inherent visual enhancements (such as low-light vision and darkvision) through the sensor.\\nIf you pay the extra cost for \"hearing\", the sensor will also pick up sounds as if you were there.\\nBy paying the cost for \"magical senses\", you can also use magically enhanced senses and detection spells through the sensor.','Scrying pool option: Instead of personally receiving the information from the sensor, you show it on a display of some sort (pool of water, crystal ball, mirror, et al). This means you can show it to others.\\nHearing option: The sensor will also pick up sounds as if you were there.\\nMagical senses option: In addition to your inherent enhancements, you can also use magical enhancements and detection spells through the sensor.\\nMobile option: The sensor can be moved at a rate of 6 squares per round. The sensor can pass through openings as small as 3 cm diameter. It cannot pass beyond the chosen range.\\nMultiple sensors option: You create up to 10 separate sensors within range.\\nSmart sensor option: You can give the sensor simple commands, and it can alert you with a mental \"ping\". For example, you can use a mobile sensor to search for a certain object or individual, or you can use multiple sensors to set up a perimeter and watch for dangerous creatures.',NULL,'If you try to scry on an individual, use the following modifiers:\\nNo knowledge: -10\\nSecond-hand knowledge: -5\\nFirst-hand knowledge: +0\\nLikeness or picture of subject: +2\\nPossession or garment: +4\\nBody part, hair, nail, etc.: +10\\nFamiliar: +5'),(162,'Secure Shelter','[Su, AoO, Force]','Arcane - Conjuration and Kinetomancy',NULL,'1 min (+0)\\n1 r (+4)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','3 PP\\n+2 PP for servant','Close (+0; PoE)','1 day (D; +0)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','Sphere; 4 sq rad (+0)','The basic spell creates an immobile sphere of force (typically half above ground and half below). The sphere maintains a comfortable temperature (20 degrees C) and protects against the elements (rain, dust, sandstorms et al) but does not keep out creatures, weapons, or magical effects. A temperature below -20 C or above 40 C or a hurricane force wind (40 m/s or more) will overload the sphere and destroy it instantly.\\nThe sphere is transparent from within but can be made opaque (any chosen color) from the outside.\\nThe caster can illuminate the interior dimly at will.\\nServant: The spell includes a simple, mindless force that can act as a servant (fetch things, clean, mend, move furniture, open doors, etc).','Lodge option: You create a small (2x2 squares) cottage or lodge inside the sphere of force. It can be made to look like a stone, timber, or even sod dwelling, but it always has the strength of a stone building. The lodge has a sturdy door (with a lock), two barred windows, a fireplace (the chimney is protected by a grate), 8 bunks, a table, 8 tools, and a writing desk.\\nServant option: The spell includes a simple, mindless force that can act as a servant (fetch things, clean, mend, move furniture, open doors, etc).',NULL,NULL),(163,'Sense Link','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind, Telepathy]','Divine - Animals and Insight (target animal only)\\nPsi - Telepathy','(d20 + Cha mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Will)','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','3 PP for one sense\\n+4 PP per add. sense','Medium (+0; LoS)','Concentration (+0)\\nEncounter (D; +2)\\nOngoing (+6; 1 PP/h)','1 creature (+0)','You link one of your own senses with that of the target; you either sense what the target is sensing or vice versa. You can use your own senses normally, regardless of whether they are linked to someone else or not. Once the link has been established, distance to the target is no longer important.\\nYou enjoy the benefits as well as penalties of the linked senses. A gaze attack, for example, can take effect through a sight link.',NULL,'S - You successfully link your senses with those of the target.\\nF - You fail to affect the target.',NULL),(164,'Shadow Creature','[Su, AoO, Dark]','Arcane - Illumination and Illusion\\nCleric Affinity - Darkness Domain\\nShadowdancing','d20 + Int mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Will','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP\\n+2 PP per creature CL\\n+4 PP for greater shadows\\n+8 PP for shades','Close (+0; PoE)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','Shadow creature(s) (+0)','The basic spell uses shadowstuff to create one or more quasi-real creatures that obey your commands. The creatures have only 20% as many HP, SP, and PP as real creatures of that type. Their natural DR is also just 20% of a regular creature. Opponents that recognize the shadow creatures\' quasi-real nature (typically because your attack fails to beat their Will) suffer less damage from their attacks. Such opponents take only 20% damage from attacks that cause HP, SP, or PP damage, while other attacks have only a 20% chance of working at all. Objects and mindless creatures automatically disbelieve the shadow creatures.\\nGreater shadows: The shadow creatures are 60% real instead of 20%.\\nShades: The shadow creatures are 80% real instead of 20%.','Simulacrum option: Instead of choosing a certain creature type, you create a quasi-real duplicate of another creature within the spell\'s range. You must pay the full PP cost, based on the original\'s CL. The caster should make a Disguise check to determine how good the likeness is.\\nGreater shadows option: The shadow creatures are 60% real instead of 20%.\\nShades option: The shadow creatures are 80% real instead of 20%.\\nMount option: Instead of a \"normal\" creature, you conjure a horselike mount of Large size. It is black and gray, somewhat insubstantial, and completely soundless. It comes equipped with saddle, bit, and bridle, and it carries up to 10 kg per skill level. It makes no attacks, but most normal animals shun it and refuse to attack it.\\nShadow mount (DeC 14; DR 4; HP 7 + skill level; Spd 3 x skill level)\\nLevitating mount option: Same as mount option, but the creature can move across sand, mud, swamps, water, and other liquid or semiliquid surfaces without difficulty.\\nWatchdog option: Instead of a \"normal\" creature, you conjure a shadow watchdog that guards you and attacks your enemies. It is invisible to everyone but yourself, and it can both detect and attack invisible and ethereal creatures. It barks when any intruder comes within 6 squares and attacks as directed by you.\\nShadow Watchdog (DeC 16; HP 20 + skill level; +10 attack - 2d6+3 HP piercing; invisible)\\nFlying mount option: Same as mount option, but the mount can fly at base speed with average maneuverability.','S - The shadow creatures have full effect against the target.\\nF - The shadow creatures have only their limited effect against the target.',NULL),(165,'Shadow Evocation','[Su, MR, AoO, Dark]','Arcane - Illumination and Illusion\\nShadowdancing','d20 + Int mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Will','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','x PP (as per duplicated spell)\\n+4 PP for greater shadow\\n+8 PP for shades','As per duplicated spell','As per duplicated spell','As per duplicated spell','The basic spell uses shadowstuff to duplicate a spell of a different type. The duplicated spell looks and works normally against creatures who believe it is real, but opponents who recognize the spell\'s quasi-real nature (typically because your attack fails to beat their Will) suffer less damage from it. Such opponents take only 20% damage from effects that cause HP, SP, or PP damage, while other effects have only a 20% chance of working at all. Objects and mindless creatures automatically disbelieve the spell.\\nSpells that can be duplicated include Bolt of Acid, Bolt of Death, Bolt of Fire, Bolt of Ice, Bolt of Lightning, Bolt of Radiance, Bolt of Sound, Create Object, Create Wall, Create Web, Fog Cloud, Ice Storm, and Wall of Energy.\\nNote that many duplicated spells will require a second attack roll (as per the duplicated spell).\\nGreater shadows: The spell is 60% real instead of 20%.\\nShades: The spell is 80% real instead of 20%.','Greater shadows option: The spell is 60% real instead of 20%.\\nShades option: The spell is 80% real instead of 20%.','S - The target suffers full effect from the illusion.\\nF - The target suffers only the reduced effect.',NULL),(166,'Shapechange','[Su, MR, AoO]','Arcane - Transmutation\\nPsi - Psychometabolism (target you only)\\nWild Shape','((d20 + Dex mod + Weapons - Natural skill mod + MAM + AB + others mods vs. DeC)\\nand then d20 + Con mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Fort)','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','3 PP for grade I\\n+2 PP for grade II\\n+8 PP for grade III\\n+10 PP for grade IV\\n+4 PP for multiple uses\\n+4 PP for mental change','Personal or Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','You (+0)\\n1 creature (+4)\\n2 creatures (+6)\\n3-4 creatures (+8)\\n5-8 creatures (+10)\\n9-16 creatures (+12)\\nUnwilling target(s) (+2)\\nNon-mag. object(s) (+2)','You alter the appearance and/or physical form of the target or targets.\\nGrade I: You can perform a single grade I shapechange of the target(s).\\nGrade II: You can perform a single grade II shapechange of the target(s).\\nGrade III: You can perform a single grade III shapechange of the target(s).\\nGrade IV: You can perform a single grade IV shapechange of the target(s).\\nMultiple uses: The target(s) can perform multiple shapechanges. Each change requires just 2 AP.\\nMental change: If you are making a grade II or III shapechange and succeed on a (d20 + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + Wis mod vs. Will) check, the target\'s mental ability scores, alignment, and personality will also change.','Grade I option: You can perform a single grade I shapechange of the target(s).\\nGrade II option: You can perform a single grade II shapechange of the target(s).\\nGrade III option: You can perform a single grade III shapechange of the target(s).\\nGrade IV option: You can perform a single grade IV shapechange of the target(s).\\nPlant form option: You can turn the target(s) into plants of Large size (shrubs or trees). A creature in plant form has its normal HP, a natural DR of 4, +10 critical hit resistance, and is immobile (Dex and speed 0) but can still see, hear, and smell normally.\\nGaseous form option: You can turn the target(s) into gaseous form.\\nStatue form option: You can turn the target(s) into solid stone statues. A creature in statue form has its normal HP, a natural DR of 8, +20 critical hit resistance, and is immobile (Dex and speed 0) but can still see, hear, and smell normally. If the creature normally consists of flesh, its mass triples.\\nMultiple uses options: The target(s) can perform multiple shapechanges. Each change requires just 2 AP.\\nMental change option: If you are making a grade II or III shapechange and succeed on a (d20 + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + Wis mod vs. Will) check, the target\'s mental ability scores, alignment, and personality will also change.\\nOak body option: The target gains a natural DR of 5 and becomes immune to ability damage, blindness, deafness, disease, drowning, poison, stunning, and other similar effects. It also takes only 1/2 damage from cold but becomes vulnerable to fire. It gains a +4 enhancement bonus to Str but take a -2 enhancement penalty to Dex. The target does not (and actually can\'t) breathe, eat, or drink, but it can still speak.\\nStone body option: Same as statue form option, but the target can still move and act. However, its base speed is halved, and it suffers a natural encumbrance class of 8. It gains immunity to blindness, deafness, ability damage, disease, poison, and stunning. It takes 1/4 damage from cold and 1/2 damage from fire and electricity. It does not need to (and actually can\'t) breathe, drink, or eat. The creature gains a +4 enhancement bonus to Str but suffers a -4 penalty to Dex (to a minimum of 1). Finally, damage caused by its natural weapons increases by two steps.\\nForm of doom option: You turn the target(s) into nightmarish versions of themselves, with writhing tentacles growing from their backs. The targets gain the frightful presence ability, a +5 natural DR bonus, +4 bonus to Str, and a +1 bonus to speed. Four of the tentacles are large enough to make melee attacks within normal reach, with a base damage of 2d8 HP.\\nIron body option: Same as stone body option, but the target\'s body turns into iron. It gains a natural DR of 10, enjoys a +6 enhancement bonus to Str, but suffers a -6 penalty to Dex and a natural encumbrance class of 10. A creature of iron weighs 8 times as much as one of flesh.\\nShadow body option ([Necrotic]): You turn the target into an insubstantial shadow (+15 to Hide checks in dim light or darkness). It has its normal speed but can move across any surface, including walls and ceilings. It cannot attack physically or manipulate physical objects, but it can still cast spells and use mental powers. It gains a natural DR of 10, +20 critical hit resistance, and darkvision, and it gains immunity to ability damage, disease, drowning, and poison. It takes only 1/2 damage from acid, electricity, and fire.','S - The target is stunned for 1 round (while fighting the transformation).\\nES - You successfully polymorph the target.\\nF - The target resists.','Potentially fatal shapechange of unwilling target: -4'),(167,'Slay Living','[Su, MR, AoO, Necrotic]','Arcane - Necromancy\\nDivine - Death','(Tch: d20 + Dex mod + Weapons - Natural skill mod + MAM + AB + others mods vs. DeC and then)\\nd20 + Con mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Fort','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nM (500+ sp of powdered black pearl)','9 PP\\n+4 PP for destruction','0 or Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)\\nMedium (+6; LoS)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 living creature (+0)\\nLiving creatures in spherical burst; 8 sq rad (+4), 12 sq rad (+8)','You overwhelm the target creature with necrotic energy, slaying it instantly. Creatures whose TL is greater than your skill level are immune to the full death effect but can still suffer the \'failure\' effect.\\nBy paying the extra cost, the remains of targets that die (but not their equipment) are completely obliterated.','Destruction option: If the target dies, its remains (but not its equipment) are completely obliterated.','S - The target creature suffers 10d6 HP of necrotic damage.\\nES - The target creature dies.\\nF - The target creature suffers 5d6 HP of necrotic damage.\\nCF - The target is unaffected.',NULL),(168,'Sleep','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind, Sleep]','Arcane - Enchantment\\nPsi - Telepathy\\nBardic Music','d20 + Cha mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Will','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP','Close (+0; LoS)\\nMedium (+3; LoS)','Concentration (+0)\\nEncounter (D; +2)\\nOngoing (+6; 1 PP/h)','1 living creature (+0)\\nLiving creatures in spherical burst; 2 sq rad (+2), 3 sq rad (+4)','Causes the target to fall into a magical slumber. Normal noise will not wake the creature, but wounding or lots of movement will do so. 6 AP can be spent to wake a creature by slapping or shaking.',NULL,'S - The target is dazed for 1 round.\\nES - You cause the target to fall asleep.\\nCS - The effect\'s duration increases by one step for free.\\nF - The target becomes drowsy and inattentive, taking a -5 penalty on Perception checks for the rest of the encounter.\\nOF - The target is unaffected.',NULL),(169,'Snow Storm','[Su, MR, AoO, Cold]','Arcane - Hydromancy\\nDivine - Elements and Nature',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','3 PP','Medium (+0; PoE)\\nLong (+3; PoE)','1 r (+0)\\nEncounter (D; +4)\\nOngoing (+8; 1 PP/h)','Cylinder; 4 sq rad, 8 sq high (+0); 8 sq rad, 8 sq high (+4)','You conjure a severe snow storm in the chosen area. It blocks all sight (including darkvision) for the duration. The area is also considered obstructed (double movement cost) due to the ice, but all such effects disappear as soon as the spell ends.','Ice storm option: The storm deals 3d6 HP of blunt damage and 2d6 HP of cold damage (per round) to all creatures and objects in the area.',NULL,NULL),(170,'Sonic Disruption','[Su, MR, AoO, Sonic]','Arcane - Aeromancy and Kinetomancy\\nDivine - Elements\\nBardic Music','d20 + Con mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Fort','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','3 PP for 4d6 HP\\n+3 PP per additional 1d6 HP','0 (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoE)','Instantaneous (+0)','Solid objects in 1 sq radius spread (+0)\\n1 crystalline creat. (+0)\\n6 sq conical burst (+4)\\n8 sq radius spread (+8)\\n12 sq conical burst (+10)','The basic spell uses noise to break or at least damage the target objects.','Sympathetic vibration option: You bypass the DR of any targeted objects.','S - You cause sonic damage to the target.\\nCS - The target takes double damage.\\nF - The target takes half damage.\\nCF - The target takes no damage.',NULL),(171,'Split Personality','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind]','Psi - Telepathy','(d20 + Dex mod + Weapons - Natural skill mod + MAM + AB + others mods vs. DeC)\\nand then d20 + Cha mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mo