otect you and attack your opponents, and if you can communicate with them, you can ask them to perform other actions.\\nSummoned creatures are unable to use their own conjuration and summoning powers, and they are also unable to use powers for teleportation and extraplanar travel.\\nWhen the spell ends or the creatures die, they (and their equipment) return to their home plane.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(175,'Summon Tentacles','[Su, AoO]','Arcane - Conjuration\\nCleric Affinity - Slime Domain',NULL,'1 r (+0)\\n9 AP (+4)\\n6 AP (+10)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','7 PP','Close (+0; PoE)\\nMedium (+3; PoE)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)','Circular spread; 4 sq rad (+0), 6 sq rad (+4)','You conjure a field of black, rubbery tentacles from any horizontal surface. Each tentacle is 3 m (or 2 squares) long and tries to grasp and crush any creature within reach. The mass of tentacles makes one grapple attack per round against every creature within the spell\'s area.\\nThe spell\'s area counts as obstructed (double movement cost), even for creatures not currently grappled.\\nTentacles (Grapple attack +18; 1d6+4 HP of grappling damage; immune to all damage)',NULL,NULL,NULL),(176,'Summon Vermin','[Su, AoO]','Divine - Animals\\nCleric Affinity - Cavern Domain\\nCleric Affinity - Spider Domain',NULL,'1 r (+0)\\n9 AP (+4)\\n6 AP (+10)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','3 PP per swarm','Close (+0; PoE)\\nMedium (+3; PoE)\\nLong (+6; PoE)','Concentration (+0)\\nEncounter (D; +4)','Rat swarm (+0)\\nBat swarm (+0)\\nSpider swarm (+0)\\nLocust swarm (+2)\\nCentipede swarm (+4)','You call forth one or more swarms of centipedes, insects, spiders, rats, or bats (see Creature chapter). While you are within range, you can control the swarm\'s movement.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(177,'Telekinesis','[Su, MR, AoO, Force]','Arcane - Kinetomancy\\nPsi - Psychokinesis\\nCleric Affinity - Magic Domain','d20 + Dex mod + weapon skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Will/Ref/DC','9