e to spend the action time and PP for that spell as well. Use the range of the Telepathy spell.',NULL,'You know the target well: +5\\nYou have met the target before: +0\\nYou have only heard of the target: -5\\nYou know nothing about the target: -10\\nLikeness or picture of target: +2\\nPossession or garment of target: +4\\nBody part, lock of hair, etc. of target: +10'),(179,'Teleport','[Su, MR, AoO, Teleport]','Arcane - Ouranomancy\\nDivine - Protection and Summoning\\nPsi - Psychoportation','Spellcasting check vs. base DC 20\\n(d20 + Cha mod + Body & Mind skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. Will)','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','5 PP for close range\\n+2 PP for long range\\n+4 PP for unlimited','Personal or Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)\\nMedium (+6; LoS)','Instantaneous (+0)','You (+0)\\n1 creature/object (+2)\\n2 creatures/objects (+4)\\n3-4 creatures/objects (+6)\\n5-8 creatures/objects (+8)\\n9-16 creatures/objects (+10)','You instantly transport the target and its equipment to any location within the specified range. Regardless of the number of targets, the total mass is limited to 25 kg per skill level.\\nUnlimited: You can teleport the target to any location in the same plane.','Unlimited option: You can teleport the target to any location in the same plane.\\nTime hop option (req Arcane - Ouranomancy or Psi - Psychoportation): You can also teleport the target forward in time up to 1 round per skill level.\\nGreater time hop option (req Arcane - Ouranomancy or Psi - Psychoportation): Same as time hop, but the maximum time is 1 hour per skill level.\\nTrigger object option (req Arcane - Ouranomancy or Divine - Protection): You store the teleport in a trigger object worth at least 150 gp (e.g. gem, rod, necklace, statuette). If the object is destroyed while speaking a command word (chosen at the time of casting), the teleport effect triggers. The teleport can have one of the following three effects, also chosen at the time of casting:\\n1. The creature breaking the object teleports to a pre-chosen destination\\n2. The creature breaking the object teleports to the caster\'s current location\\n3. The caster teleports to the location of the creature breaking the object.\\nIn all three cases, the destination has to be within the spell\'s range, or nothing happens.','If a target is unwilling, an attack against Will is required:\\nS - You fail to teleport the target but can choose to bodily scramble it for 4d6 HP of damage.\\nES - You can either teleport the target or bodily scramble it for 9d6 HP of damage.\\nF - You fail to affect the target\\nThe result of the spellcasting check:\\nS - You teleport the target to the desired location.\\nF - You teleport the target to the wrong destination. Roll 1d10 for specific result: 1-5 - Off target by 1d10x10% of the total distance; 6-8 - Target ends up in similar area; 9-10 - Target(s) take 1d10 HP of damage and roll again for actual destination.\\nOF - The teleportation simply fails.','Very familiar destination: +0\\nStudied destination carefully: -2\\nSeen destination casually: -4\\nViewed destination once: -6'),(180,'Teleportation Circle','[Su, AoO, Teleport]','Arcane - Ouranomancy\\nPsi - Psychoportation','Spellcasting check vs. base DC 20','10 min (+0)\\n1 min (+4)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nM (100 gp of amber)','15 PP for long range\\n+2 PP for unlimited\\n+2 PP for limited trigger\\n+2 PP for two-way\\n+2 PP for variable destination','Tch (+0)','Ongoing (+0; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +4; 100 XP cost per PL)','Circular area; up to 1 sq rad (+0), 2 sq rad (+4), 3 sq rad (+8)','You create an invisible circle on a horizontal surface. Any creature or object entering the circle is teleported to a destination (within long range) chosen at the time of casting.\\nEach round, the circle can teleport a maximum of 25 kg per skill level.\\nUnlimited: The destination can be any location in the same plane.\\nLimited trigger: The circle will o