r), the foreign soul will still leave the occupied body. Bodies that end up without a soul when the spell ends start to die.\\nIf you pay for a \"swap\", the souls in the source and destination swap places.','Swap option: The souls in the source and destination swap places.','S - The target is stunned for 1 round (while fighting the intruding soul).\\nES - The target is affected.\\nF - The target is unaffected.',NULL),(185,'Transform Seeds','[Su, AoO]','Divine - Plants',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nF (divine focus)','1 PP','Tch (+0)','Ongoing (+0; 1 PP/h)','4 berries/acorns (+0)\\n16 berries/acorns (+4)','The basic spell enchants a number of berries and acorns so that each of them provides as much nourishment as a normal meal and also heals 2 SP and 1 HP of damage. A single creature can enjoy the healing benefits of up to 8 berries per 24 hours.','Bomb seeds option [Fire]: Instead of creating nourishing berries, you turn the seeds into special bombs. If you are within 40 squares and speak a command word, each seed instantly bursts into flame, causing 1d8+skill level HP of fire damage and igniting combustibles in a burst of 1 square radius. Make a +10 attack against every affected creature\'s Ref; if the attack fails, the creature takes only half damage.\\nFire seeds option [Fire]: Instead of creating nourishing berries, you turn the seeds into special grenades. The base throwing range of each grenade is 4 squares and requires a normal ranged attack roll. A grenade that strikes a hard surface (including most creatures) explodes and causes 5d6 HP of fire damage to the target. The explosion also deals 10 HP of splash damage in a burst of 2 squares radius.',NULL,NULL),(186,'Transmute Metal','[Su, MR, AoO]','Divine - Elements\\nCleric Affinity - Metal Domain',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP','Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)\\nMedium (+6; LoS)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 ferrous object/creature (up to 1 m rad volume; +0)\\nSpherical burst, 4 sq rad (+4), 8 sq rad (+8)','The basic spell heats non-magical metal objects (or parts of them), turning them glowing hot for 10 rounds. Touching a heated object (or being struck by a heated weapon) causes 1d4 HP of fire damage. As usual, you need a successful attack in order to affect objects held or worn by an unwilling opponent.','Transmute to wood: This version of the spell transmutes non-magical metal objects to wood.\\nRusting grasp: Instead of transmuting metal to wood, this version causes non-magical ferrous objects to become severely rusted, effectively destroying them.\\nThe spell causes 6d6+10 HP of damage against ferrous creatures.',NULL,NULL),(187,'Transmute Rock','[Su, AoO, Earth]','Arcane - Lithomancy and Transmutation\\nDivine - Elements and Nature',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP','Close (+0; LoS)\\nMedium (+3; LoS)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','Cube; 2x2x2 sq (+0)\\n8 x PL cubes (S; +4)','This spell alters the character, consistency, or very nature of stone-based matter (including sand, rock, most minerals, most crystals, etc).\\nThe basic spell makes a stone surface extremely slippery for the chosen duration. Creatures in the area have to make Balance checks against DC 10 to move (at 1/2 speed) and avoid falling down.','Soften option: You soften natural (unworked) earth and rock in the area. Wet earth becomes mud, dry earth becomes sand, and stone becomes soft clay. This is typically not sufficient to trap creatures, but the area becomes difficult terrain, and the spell can cause a small landslide.\\nSpike stones option: You turn a stone surface into a mass of hard and sharp spikes. Its appearance does not change, but it becomes difficult terrain and causes 1d8 HP of damage for every square that a creature moves on foot through the area. Furthermore, if a +10 attack roll succeeds against a creature injured by the spikes, its movement is halved for 24 h (as per caltrop wounds).\\nStone shape option: This version lets you reshape a stone object into any shape you wish. The object must not weigh more than 10 kg per skill level. Fine details or moving parts will require a suitable Crafting check.\\nMud to stone option: Turns normal mud or quicksand into soft stone (sandstone, for example). Creatures in the mud suffer a +15 attack against Ref to avoid getting stuck.\\nStone to mud option: Turns natural (unworked) stone into mud, to a maximum depth of two squares. Turning the ground into mud turns it into very difficult terrain. Turning a cliff wall or a cavern ceiling into mud will usually cause a mudslide.',NULL,NULL),(188,'Transmute Wood','[Su, AoO]','Divine - Plant\\nCleric Affinity - Craft Domain',NULL,'10 min (+0)\\n1 min (+4)\\n1 r (+10)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP','Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)','Ongoing (+0; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +4; 100 XP cost per PL)','1 wooden object (+0)\\nWooden objects in 4 sq radius sphere (+4)','The basic spell lets you reshape a wooden object into any shape you wish. The object must not weigh more than 10 kg per skill level. Fine details or moving parts will require a suitable Crafting check.\\nThe basic spell can also be used to warp wooden objects, rendering them useless (or at least nearly useless).','Ironwood option: You change the object into ironwood, a substance that is still wood but has the density, strength, resilience, and resistances of steel.',NULL,NULL),(189,'Ventriloquism','[Su, AoO, Lang, Illusion]','Arcane - Illusion\\nBardic Music',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP','Medium (+0; PoE)\\nLong (+3; PoE)\\nUnlimited (+6)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','Sound or speech (+0)','This spell lets you throw your voice (and other naturally produced sounds) to locations within range.\\nThe basic spell can also be used to project your voice to one or more creatures within range. They all hear your speech (or whispered messages) as if you were standing right next to them.','Triggered option: You record a spoken message and place the spell on an object or in an area and specify a trigger condition. When the condition is fulfilled, the message starts and continues for up to the chosen duration.',NULL,NULL),(190,'Wall of Energy','[Su, MR, AoO]','Arcane - Aeromancy (Wall of Lightning and Sonic Wall)\\nArcane - Hydromancy (Wall of Acid and Wall of Ice)\\nArcane - Pyromancy (Wall of Fire)\\nArcane - Necromancy (Necrotic Wall)\\nArcane - Illumination (Radiant Wall)\\nDivine - Elements (Wall of Lightning, Fire, or Ice)\\nDivine - Death (Necrotic Wall)\\nDivine - Life (Radiant Wall)\\nPsi - Metacreativity and Psychokinesis (Wall of Acid, Fire, Ice, Lightning, or Sound)',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','7 PP','Medium (+0; PoE)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','Vertical wall 4 x level sq long and 4 sq high (+0)\\nVertical circular wall 1 x level sq diameter and 4 sq high (+0)','You create an immobile, shimmering barrier of the chosen energy type. The sonic wall is transparent and hard to detect visually (treat as invisible), but the other wall types are opaque and provide total concealment in both directions. One side of the wall, chosen by you, radiates energy and causes 2d4 HP of damage per round within 2 squares and 1d4 HP per round from 3 to 4 squares away. Creatures that pass through the wall (and those positioned where it appears) take (2d6 + skill level) HP of energy damage.\\nThe wall of ice normally consists of frigid air, but the caster can choose to create it as a solid sheet of ice, up to 2 cm thick per skill level. This is only possible if the chosen area is unoccupied by objects and creatures, and the ice sheet must be anchored to either a floor or two opposing walls.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(191,'Wall of Thorns','[Su, AoO]','Divine - Plants',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','5 PP','Medium (+0; PoE)\\nLong (+3; PoE)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','Wall of thorns, 8 x level cubes (S; +0)','You create a barrier of very tough and thorny brush anchored to the ground. The barrier counts as very difficult terrain, and creatures moving through the wall take 10 HP of piercing damage per square moved (reduced by DR).',NULL,NULL,NULL),(192,'Zone of Revelation','[Su, MR, AoO, Mind]','Divine - Insight\\nPsi - Clairsentience and Telepathy',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP','0 (+0)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','Spherical emanation; 4 sq rad (+0), 8 sq rad (+4), 12 sq rad (+8)','You create an aura in which deception becomes much more difficult.\\nUnless a creature\'s Will beats 10 + the spell\'s PL, it is unable to speak any deliberate lies.','Invisibility purge option: The aura also temporarily disables any invisibility effect of a lower PL.',NULL,NULL),(193,'Touch of Acid','[Su, MR, AoO, Acid]','Arcane - Hydromancy\\nPsi - Psychometabolism','d20 + Dex mod + Natural Weapon skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. DeC','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP for 3d6 HP\\n+3 PP per additional 1d6 HP','Tch (+0)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 target (+0)','You attack the target with a touch of acid.',NULL,'S - The target takes the indicated amount of damage.\\nCS - The target takes double damage.\\nF - You hit with a glancing touch that deals half damage\\nEF - You miss the target.',NULL),(194,'Touch of Death','[Su, MR, AoO, Necrotic]','Arcane - Necromancy\\nDivine - Death\\nPsi - Psychometabolism','d20 + Dex mod + Natural Weapon skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. DeC','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP for 3d6 HP/SP\\n+3 PP per additional 1d6','Tch (+0)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 target (+0)','You attack the target with a touch of necrotic energy. You can divide the d6s of damage any way you want between HP and SP.','Strength drain option: A successful attack also causes 2 points of ability damage to Str.\\nVampiric option: You gain the necrotic damage dealt as temporary HP and SP. If the damage kills a target creature, you also gain a +2 bonus on all action checks for the rest of the encounter.','S - The target takes the indicated amount of damage.\\nCS - The target takes double damage.\\nF - You hit with a glancing touch that deals half damage\\nEF - You miss the target.',NULL),(195,'Touch of Fire','[Su, MR, AoO, Fire]','Arcane - Pyromancy\\nPsi - Psychokinesis (+2 PP cost)','d20 + Dex mod + Natural Weapon skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. DeC','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP for 3d6 HP\\n+3 PP per additional 1d6 HP','Tch (+0)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 target (+0)','You attack the target with a touch of fire and heat. This may set fire to unattended, flammable objects.',NULL,'S - The target takes the indicated amount of damage.\\nCS - The target takes double damage.\\nF - You hit with a glancing touch that deals half damage\\nEF - You miss the target.',NULL),(196,'Touch of Ice','[Su, MR, AoO, Cold]','Arcane - Hydromancy\\nPsi - Psychokinesis (+2 PP cost)','d20 + Dex mod + Natural Weapon skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. DeC','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP for 3d6 HP/SP\\n+3 PP per additional 1d6','Tch (+0)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 target (+0)','You attack the target with a touch of intense cold. You can divide the d6s of damage any way you want between HP and SP. Note that such intense cold can instantaneously freeze most water-based liquids.',NULL,'S - The target takes the indicated amount of damage.\\nCS - The target takes double damage.\\nF - You hit with a glancing touch that deals half damage\\nEF - You miss the target.',NULL),(197,'Touch of Lightning','[Su, MR, AoO, Electricity]','Arcane - Aeromancy\\nPsi - Psychokinesis (+2 PP cost)','d20 + Dex mod + Natural Weapon skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. DeC','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP for 3d6 HP/SP\\n+3 PP per additional 1d6','Tch (+0)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 target (+0)','You attack the target with a touch of electricity. You can divide the d6s of damage any way you want between HP and SP.',NULL,'S - The target takes the indicated amount of damage.\\nCS - The target takes double damage.\\nF - You hit with a glancing touch that deals half damage\\nEF - You miss the target.',NULL),(198,'Touch of Radiance','[Su, MR, AoO, Radiant]','Arcane - Illumination\\nDivine - Life and Retribution','d20 + Dex mod + Natural Weapon skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. DeC','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP for 3d6 HP\\n+3 PP per additional 1d6 HP','Tch (+0)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 target (+0)','You attack the target with a touch of intense radiance.',NULL,'S - The target takes the indicated amount of damage.\\nCS - The target takes double damage.\\nF - You hit with a glancing touch that deals half damage\\nEF - You miss the target.',NULL),(199,'Touch of Sound','[Su, MR, AoO, Sonic]','Arcane - Aeromancy\\nPsi - Psychokinesis (+2 PP cost)\\nBardic Music','d20 + Dex mod + Natural Weapon skill mod + MAM + AB + other mods vs. DeC','9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP for 3d6 HP/SP\\n+3 PP per additional 1d6','Tch (+0)','Instantaneous (+0)','1 target (+0)','You attack the target with a touch of sonic concussion. You can divide the d6s of damage any way you want between HP and SP.','Deafening option: A successful attack also deafens the target for the rest of the encounter.\\nStunning option: A successful attack also stuns the target for 1 round.','S - The target takes the indicated amount of damage.\\nCS - The target takes double damage.\\nF - You hit with a glancing touch that deals half damage\\nEF - You miss the target.',NULL),(200,'Silver Storm','[Su, MR, AoO, Earth]','Arcane - Lithomancy\\nDivine - Elements',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','3 PP','Close (+0; LoE)\\nMedium (+3; LoE)','1 r (+0)\\nEncounter (D; +4)\\nOngoing (+8; 1 PP/h)','Circular spread; 4 sq rad (+0), 6 sq rad (+4)','You conjure a swirling cloud of silver particles in the chosen area. The particles cling to (and reveal) both invisible and incorporeal creatures; they also glow slightly and negate penalties due to non-magical darkness or dim light. These effects last only while a creature remains within the cloud.\\nWhile within the area, a creature suffers 1d6 SP per round (due to suffocation) and is automatically dazzled. Creatures sensitive to silver also suffer 1d10 HP of damage per round.','Needles option: The silver particles become needles that deal an additional 5d6 HP of continuous piercing damage per round. Against creatures sensitive to silver the damage increases to 5d10 HP.',NULL,NULL),(201,'Enchant Armor','[Su, AoO]','Arcane - Abjuration and Transmutation\\nDivine - Protection\\nPsi - Metacreativity',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP per total PL','Tch (+0)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','1 armor (+0)','Enchants a suit of armor (or even clothing) with an enhancement bonus to DR and/or other special effects (those item modifications that have armor as preferred item type).\\nThe casting costs 1 PP per resulting PL of the armor (see the item modification list for possible effects and their PL). If the armor is already magical, add its PL to calculate the cost of the spell. You must also know the spells specified for the desired effect(s).',NULL,NULL,NULL),(202,'Enchant Focus','[Su, AoO]','Arcane - Transmutation\\nDivine - Retribution\\nPsi - Metacreativity',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP per total PL','Tch (+0)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','1 focus (+0)','Enchants a focus with an enhancement bonus to attack and damage. Other effects can also be added, specifically those item modifications that have a focus as preferred item type.\\nThe casting costs 1 PP per resulting PL of the focus (see the item modification list for possible effects and their PL). If the focus is already magical, add its PL to calculate the cost of the spell. You must also know the spells specified for the desired effect(s).',NULL,NULL,NULL),(203,'Enchant Shield','[Su, AoO]','Arcane - Abjuration and Transmutation\\nDivine - Protection\\nPsi - Metacreativity',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP per total PL','Tch (+0)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','1 shield (+0)','Enchants a shield with an enhancement bonus to parry. Other effects can also be added, specifically those item modifications that have shield as preferred item type.\\nThe casting costs 1 PP per resulting PL of the shield (see the item modification list for possible effects and their PL). If the shield is already magical, add its PL to calculate the cost of the spell. You must also know the spells specified for the desired effect(s).',NULL,NULL,NULL),(204,'Enchant Weapon','[Su, AoO]','Arcane - Transmutation\\nDivine - Retribution\\nDivine - Animals (only for natural weapons)\\nPsi - Metacreativity (only for non-natural weapons)\\nPsi - Psychometabolism (only for natural weapons)\\nArcane Archery (only for bows and arrows)',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP per total PL','Tch (+0)','Encounter (D; +0)\\nOngoing (+4; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','1 weapon or 50 projectiles (+0)','Enchants a weapon with an enhancement bonus to attack and damage. Natural attacks can also be enchanted, but note that each attack form counts as one weapon (in other words, one casting will not enhance all of a creature\'s natural attacks). Projectiles receive only a damage bonus (not an attack bonus). Other effects can also be added, specifically those item modifications that have weapon as preferred item type.\\nThe casting costs 1 PP per resulting PL of the weapon (see the item modification list for possible effects and their PL). If the weapon is already magical, add its PL to calculate the cost of the spell. You must also know the spells specified for the desired effect(s).',NULL,NULL,NULL),(205,'Contingency','[Su, AoO]','Arcane - Abjuration and Ouranomancy\\nDivine - Protection\\nPsi - Metacreativity and Psychometabolism',NULL,'10 min (+0)\\n1 min (+4)\\n1 r (+10)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nF (small statuette worth 100 sp per PL of triggered spell)','7 PP','Personal (+0)','Ongoing (+0; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8)','You and one spell (+0)','This spell sets up a trigger condition that activates a second spell. The second spell must be cast by you directly after the Contingency spell, it must have only you as target, and it must not have a higher PP cost than half the Contingency\'s PL.\\nThe second spell will not activate nor start counting its duration until the triggering condition has been met. The spell will take effect after the triggering condition has been resolved, and it cannot be used to interrupt an ongoing action.\\nThe trigger can be based on any condition affecting your person, including bloodied, unconscious, exhausted, et. al., but it cannot trigger on exact levels of HP, SP, or PP. It can also be based on anything perceived by your senses (or recognized by your Knowledge and Linguistics skills), but it will be fooled by anything that successfully fools your senses.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(206,'Trigger','[Su, AoO]','Arcane - Abjuration and Divination\\nDivine - Insight and Protection\\nPsi - Clairsentience and Metacreativity','Special','10 min (+0)\\n1 min (+4)\\n1 r (+10)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)\\nM (powdered gems worth 100 sp per PL of triggered spell)','3 PP for touch trigger\\n+2 PP for +15 Spot\\n+2 PP for +15 Listen\\n+4 PP for +20 Spot\\n+4 PP for +20 Listen\\n+6 PP for +25 Spot\\n+6 PP for +25 Listen','Tch (+0)','Ongoing (+0; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8)','1 location or object plus one spell (+0)','This spell creates a magical touch sensor at a location or on an object, and then sets up a second spell to be activated by the sensor. The second spell must be cast by you directly after the Trigger spell, it must be centered on the target, it must target an area or the triggering creature(s) or objects present during the casting, and it must not have a higher PP cost than half the Trigger\'s PL.\\nThe second spell will not activate nor start counting its duration until the triggering condition has been met. The spell will take effect after the triggering condition has been resolved, and it cannot be used to interrupt an ongoing action. If the triggered spell involves an attack roll, replace it with d20 + (PL of the Trigger).\\nThe Trigger is invisible, but it can be detected and disabled as a magical trap of the appropriate PL.\\nThe trigger can be based on anything perceived by the sensor (recognition of creatures, words, etc. are limited by the caster\'s Knowledge and Linguistics skills), but it can potentially be fooled by invisibility and illusions.\\nSpot: The sensor has normal vision and can make reactive Spot checks.\\nListen: The sensor has normal hearing and can make reactive Listen checks.','Spot options: The sensor has normal vision and can make reactive Spot checks.\\nListen options: The sensor has normal hearing and can make reactive Listen checks.',NULL,NULL),(207,'Force Armor','[Su, MR, AoO, Force]','Arcane - Abjuration and Kinetomancy\\nPsi - Metacreativity and Psychokinesis',NULL,'9 AP (+0)\\n6 AP (+6)','V (+0), Silent (+2)\\nS (+0), Still (+2)','1 PP for +2 bonus\\n+3 PP per extra +1 (up to +10 total)','Tch (+0)\\nClose (+3; LoS)','Ongoing (+0; 1 PP/h)\\nPermanent (D; +8; 100 XP cost per PL)','1 creature (+0)\\n2 creatures (+2)\\n3-4 creatures (+4)\\n5-8 creatures (+6)\\n9-16 creatures (+8)','This spell envelops the target\'s body in a force field that provides an armor bonus to DR (without hindering movement at all).',NULL,NULL,NULL);
