INSERT INTO `targettypes` VALUES (1,'You','you       ','The action affects only you.'),(2,'Target','tgt       ','Specifies the number and types of creatures or objects that can be affected.\\nYou typically need both line of sight and line of effect to each target (unless the range specifies otherwise). Selection of a target requires no aiming and no ranged attack roll, however, and the effect only has to overcome the defense and resistance of the target(s).\\nSome actions can only affect willing targets, but unconscious creatures are automatically considered willing for such actions.'),(3,'Ray','ray       ','A ray is a ranged attack that can strike and affect a single creature or object.\\nAll of the modifiers and conditions that apply to ranged weapon attacks also apply to ray attacks.\\nA ray is always instantaneous, and any other duration specified is the duration of the effect (not of the ray itself).'),(4,'Burst','bst       ','The effect radiates the specified distance from the point of origin. It does not flow around corners, so a target\'s cover is calculated relative to the point of origin.\\nA burst is always instantaneous, and any other duration specified is the duration of the effect (not of the burst itself).'),(5,'Emanation','emn       ','The effect radiates the specified distance from the point of origin, just like a burst effect.\\nEmanations, however, are generally non-instantaneous and last for the action\'s specified duration.'),(6,'Spread','sprd      ','The effect spreads or flows out the specified distance from the point of origin. It can flow around corners, through openings, and into areas that you cannot see, but it does not penetrate solid obstructions.\\nSpreads typically last for the action\'s specified duration.'),(7,'Sphere','sph       ','A spherical volume with the point of origin at its center. Unless otherwise specified, the point of origin should be an intersection between squares.'),(8,'Cone','con       ','Has its apex at the point of origin and spreads in a 90 degree cone in any desired direction. Unless otherwise specified, the point of origin should be an intersection between squares.'),(9,'Cylinder','cyl       ','A cylinder-shaped volume with its center at the point of origin. Unless otherwise specified, the point of origin should be an intersection between squares. Many cylindrical volumes of effect have to be oriented with their circular surfaces parallel to the ground.'),(10,'Line','line      ','A narrow cylinder stretching away from the point of origin in any desired direction.\\nLine-shaped effects affect all squares that the line passes through.'),(11,'Wall','wall','Wall areas are vertical planes of a specified material, shape, size, and thickness. Wall characteristics can vary widely, but unless otherwise specified, a wall is opaque and may not have curves or corners, and if its thickness is less than 1 square, it must be placed between squares (rather than in squares).\\nCatching creatures \"under\" a wall area is usually quite hard, requiring an attack roll against Ref with exceptional success. Furthermore, many wall areas must be continuous and unbroken when formed, so creating them in a creature\'s spacing would cause them to fail.');
